WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:22.355 --> 00:26.592
[MUSIC]

00:36.703 --> 00:40.739
[TRAFFIC SOUNDS]

00:51.818 --> 00:55.821
[MUSIC ONLY]

01:39.699 --> 01:42.301
Oh, I'm such an idiot.

01:42.303 --> 01:44.069
I just left my key on the table

01:44.071 --> 01:45.237
so that I wouldn't forget it.

01:45.239 --> 01:46.738
No problem, I can let you in.

01:46.740 --> 01:48.974
Thank you so much.

01:48.976 --> 01:51.376
I do this all the time.

01:51.378 --> 01:55.380
Its really stupid of me.

01:56.282 --> 01:57.616
I hate to interrupt.

01:57.618 --> 01:59.151
[SPEAKING SPANISH] La Ciento!

01:59.153 --> 02:00.252
You're sorry?

02:00.254 --> 02:01.954
I'm his wife.

02:01.956 --> 02:03.055
I can explain.

02:03.057 --> 02:04.289
Let me give it a shot.

02:04.291 --> 02:06.091
You fell naked into bed with
your intern.

02:06.093 --> 02:08.894
Ma'am, I'm so super sorry but,

02:08.895 --> 02:12.564
Chaz and me like, really,
really love each other.

02:12.566 --> 02:14.500
That's so sweet.

02:14.502 --> 02:15.734
Get dressed!

02:15.736 --> 02:17.269
And answer your phone!

02:17.271 --> 02:21.240
I have been calling
you non-stop!

02:21.608 --> 02:23.642
Your dad's in the hospital.

02:23.644 --> 02:27.646
He's in a coma so they moved
him to Richmond.

02:31.751 --> 02:35.754
[SNICKERING]

02:37.490 --> 02:41.527
And this one says, "Feel
better" from your buddy Paul.

02:42.795 --> 02:45.130
Of course, its feel better
with Tequila.

02:45.132 --> 02:48.167
And Doris's grandson drew a
great picture of you

02:48.169 --> 02:52.204
falling off the roof
of the house.

02:54.541 --> 02:56.208
[KNOCKING]

02:56.210 --> 02:59.478
Hey...

02:59.480 --> 03:01.146
I'm glad you guys made it.

03:01.148 --> 03:02.214
Oh my gosh.

03:02.216 --> 03:03.448
Baby!

03:03.450 --> 03:04.850
What's the latest?

03:04.852 --> 03:06.818
He's going to be okay, he's
going to be okay.

03:06.820 --> 03:08.387
He's been working so hard on
the house.

03:08.389 --> 03:10.956
This coma's probably saved him
from a heart attack.

03:10.958 --> 03:12.057
Is there anything we can do?

03:12.059 --> 03:14.326
No, Ben came by and
brought the mail.

03:14.328 --> 03:15.494
Sarah's Ben?

03:15.496 --> 03:16.562
Uh-huh.

03:16.564 --> 03:17.963
Oh, he does exist.

03:17.965 --> 03:20.132
Yeah, he brought me some
clothes from the house.

03:20.134 --> 03:23.035
What is all this Grillig
Property stuff?

03:23.037 --> 03:24.403
I told you about those people.

03:24.405 --> 03:25.804
They're trying to buy up our
whole neighborhood.

03:25.806 --> 03:27.739
I'm going to go
use the bathroom.

03:27.741 --> 03:28.974
Talk to your father.

03:28.976 --> 03:32.978
Okay.

03:36.816 --> 03:38.317
I feel like I probably should

03:38.319 --> 03:40.586
stay here in Richmond with them.

03:40.588 --> 03:43.021
You're going to stay here with
my parents?

03:43.023 --> 03:44.656
Yeah, somebody has to.

03:44.658 --> 03:45.924
Your mom can't do a
three hour drive

03:45.926 --> 03:47.893
back and forth from
Bethel Cove everyday.

03:47.895 --> 03:50.395
That's not going to work,

03:50.397 --> 03:52.331
so we'll just get a hotel room
and I'll stay.

03:52.333 --> 03:54.032
So you're not going to tell
them what happened?

03:54.034 --> 03:57.102
- Eventually, yeah
- Listen Jess, I can't get
a divorce.

03:57.104 --> 04:00.339
My mom and dad
would be devastated.

04:00.341 --> 04:01.907
If its the cheating, I swear-

04:01.909 --> 04:04.276
If its the cheating?

04:04.278 --> 04:08.313
[MUSIC]

04:19.892 --> 04:21.692
It's good to see
you again, Jess.

04:21.695 --> 04:22.861
Did you bring the papers?

04:22.863 --> 04:24.429
Yeah, I did, I'll
give them to you

04:24.431 --> 04:25.797
when we get back to the house.

04:25.799 --> 04:27.733
Just mail them back to me when
you're done.

04:27.735 --> 04:29.101
And it'll be final.

04:29.103 --> 04:31.370
Jess, we have to tell her.

04:31.372 --> 04:32.571
No, not yet.

04:32.573 --> 04:33.705
Jess, she thinks she's moving
to New York

04:33.707 --> 04:34.740
to live with the both of us.

04:34.742 --> 04:36.742
I know that, but this... No.

04:36.744 --> 04:40.779
Not today.

04:41.781 --> 04:44.049
I can't believe you never
brought me to your hometown.

04:44.051 --> 04:47.119
Well, you're welcome.

04:47.121 --> 04:51.156
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

04:57.430 --> 04:59.898
Who is that arguing with her?

04:59.900 --> 05:01.900
Insurance salesman.

05:01.902 --> 05:04.469
Won't leave her alone.

05:04.471 --> 05:05.304
Are you kidding me?

05:05.306 --> 05:09.341
Here?!

05:10.009 --> 05:11.343
I'm sorry, Mr.

05:11.345 --> 05:13.111
can I take you
for a second, please?

05:13.113 --> 05:15.814
I just want to talk to you.

05:15.816 --> 05:19.851
Mom, I'm so sorry...

05:19.853 --> 05:21.019
Jessie, right?

05:21.021 --> 05:22.020
It's good to finally meet you.

05:22.022 --> 05:22.954
Save it.

05:22.956 --> 05:24.356
I saw you talking to Naomi.

05:24.358 --> 05:25.791
Of course, I'm worried about
her future.

05:25.793 --> 05:29.761
Maybe you should be worried
about your own future.

05:32.699 --> 05:36.201
You got exactly what you
deserve right there.

05:36.203 --> 05:38.770
And, if I ever catch you trying
to sell to her again,

05:38.772 --> 05:40.806
I'll teach you about a little
kick called the Kistrate.

05:40.808 --> 05:42.941
Something I learned in self
defense class.

05:42.943 --> 05:46.545
Wait, wait, wait.

05:46.547 --> 05:50.582
Stay.

05:57.223 --> 05:58.490
What happened?

05:58.492 --> 05:59.391
We talked.

05:59.393 --> 06:01.026
We just worked it out.

06:01.028 --> 06:05.063
It was very civil, very...

06:06.332 --> 06:09.401
Oh no...

06:09.403 --> 06:12.237
For those of you who
don't know me,

06:12.239 --> 06:16.241
I'm pastor Ben Kingston.

06:16.476 --> 06:20.479
I was...

06:21.214 --> 06:24.416
I was blessed to call Lyle
Ellison my father-in-law.

06:24.418 --> 06:26.051
He and Naomi are
the proud parents

06:26.053 --> 06:29.054
of Chaz and my wife, Sarah.

06:29.056 --> 06:31.990
She was the love of my life.

06:31.992 --> 06:34.659
And even after she passed six
years ago,

06:34.661 --> 06:36.661
Lyle insisted I call him Dad.

06:36.663 --> 06:37.896
And I did.

06:37.898 --> 06:41.833
Lyle is survived by his
beautiful wife Naomi...

07:01.087 --> 07:04.222
You okay, Mom?

07:04.224 --> 07:05.290
Hey guys, I got some leftovers.

07:05.292 --> 07:06.191
Shh

07:06.193 --> 07:08.026
Sorry!

07:08.028 --> 07:10.295
And I'm sorry about the grave.

07:10.297 --> 07:12.864
Chaz told me you were an
insurance salesman.

07:12.866 --> 07:14.800
That's Ben's joke.

07:14.802 --> 07:16.868
That's your joke?

07:16.870 --> 07:19.304
Life after death insurance.

07:19.306 --> 07:21.640
I'm a pastor, I help people get
in Heaven.

07:21.642 --> 07:23.975
It's not as funny when I
explain it.

07:23.977 --> 07:28.046
Ever.

07:30.416 --> 07:32.918
Mom, you okay?

07:32.920 --> 07:36.955
The mover's will take care of
all of this.

07:39.559 --> 07:42.093
I just want to pack up for
myself, okay?

07:42.095 --> 07:45.464
Just give me three or four more
weeks, please?

07:45.466 --> 07:48.733
I mean, two if Jesse will stay
and help me.

07:48.735 --> 07:52.704
Yes, yeah of course.

08:01.147 --> 08:02.681
Mom, let me just hire movers

08:02.683 --> 08:04.182
and you'll be out of here
within a week.

08:04.184 --> 08:06.117
Why are you rushing her?

08:06.119 --> 08:09.287
They won't close until she
moves out.

08:09.289 --> 08:10.956
They can't just wait a little
while longer?

08:10.958 --> 08:12.357
How many other people are going
to buy a house with a

08:12.359 --> 08:13.792
bridge in their front yard?

08:13.794 --> 08:14.926
I don't know Chaz,
but I do know

08:14.928 --> 08:15.927
that Mom doesn't want to move-

08:15.929 --> 08:16.795
She's not your Mom!

08:16.797 --> 08:18.096
We're divorced!

08:18.098 --> 08:21.032
What?

08:21.034 --> 08:21.933
Charles?

08:21.935 --> 08:24.469
Chaz, you are such a-

08:24.471 --> 08:26.371
Monkey bread?

08:26.373 --> 08:28.340
Chaz and I got a divorce.

08:28.342 --> 08:30.475
Since I've been in the kitchen?

08:30.477 --> 08:34.044
Here, do me a favor
and pack fast.

08:34.047 --> 08:35.780
The movers will be
here in two weeks.

08:35.782 --> 08:37.948
And that's longer than you want
to be in this town.

08:37.951 --> 08:41.520
Trust me.

08:41.522 --> 08:44.489
Bye.

08:44.491 --> 08:48.527
I'm going to take care of my
own luggage...

08:49.328 --> 08:52.998
Naomi, are you sure this is a
good idea?

08:53.000 --> 08:55.367
My son wants me to
move in with him,

08:55.369 --> 08:56.535
I'm not going to say, "No."

08:56.537 --> 08:59.371
No, I mean that, too, but,
never mind!

08:59.373 --> 09:02.140
He means letting me
stay with you.

09:02.142 --> 09:06.144
That is not what I meant.

09:07.046 --> 09:10.682
That's what I meant.

09:10.684 --> 09:11.583
Jim Nuefert?

09:11.585 --> 09:12.918
Chaz Ellison here.

09:12.920 --> 09:14.853
[ON PHONE] Hey Hardball, what's
going on?

09:14.855 --> 09:15.987
Do we have a deal?

09:15.989 --> 09:17.389
Absolutely, just need
a couple weeks

09:17.391 --> 09:20.559
to finalize the paperwork and
we're all set.

09:20.561 --> 09:22.761
That's cutting it close.

09:22.763 --> 09:24.729
Listen man, two weeks and
they're out of the house.

09:24.731 --> 09:28.767
Guaranteed.

09:38.010 --> 09:41.580
Curly fries, you got it.

09:41.582 --> 09:44.349
- I'll have that right out
for you
- Daphne Larkin,

09:44.351 --> 09:46.284
I was hoping you'd
still be here.

09:46.286 --> 09:50.322
Always here for you, Chaz.

09:50.590 --> 09:51.957
I was sorry to hear
about your dad.

09:51.959 --> 09:53.558
Thank you.

09:53.560 --> 09:54.960
Can I get you something?

09:54.962 --> 09:56.761
Do you remember what
I used to like?

09:56.763 --> 09:58.296
Of course I do.

09:58.298 --> 09:59.965
I'm assuming you want it to go?

09:59.967 --> 10:01.800
Actually, I was going to eat it
here if you don't mind?

10:01.802 --> 10:02.968
Oh yeah, pull up a seat.

10:02.970 --> 10:07.038
Great.

10:13.212 --> 10:16.915
If only I'd known you'd be this
hot twenty years later.

10:16.917 --> 10:20.885
Careful, you're a
married man, again.

10:21.253 --> 10:23.622
And divorced again?

10:23.624 --> 10:25.223
No, I thought she was in town
here with you.

10:25.225 --> 10:27.792
She is, she's over there
with my mom.

10:27.794 --> 10:29.628
Practically moving in with her.

10:29.630 --> 10:31.429
She still thinks
there's a chance.

10:31.431 --> 10:33.898
No, done deal.

10:33.900 --> 10:34.733
Why is that?

10:34.735 --> 10:35.967
What did she cheat on you?

10:35.969 --> 10:38.236
I really shouldn't say.

10:38.238 --> 10:40.605
Really?

10:40.607 --> 10:44.643
Listen, Daphne,
I'm flying out tonight.

10:45.244 --> 10:47.846
Maybe you could
check in on her?

10:47.848 --> 10:51.883
Make sure she doesn't get too
comfortable here?

10:52.518 --> 10:55.787
Thanks, Daphne.

10:55.789 --> 10:57.255
Alright, I got to
get to my customers.

10:57.257 --> 11:01.326
Quit being so charming.

11:07.800 --> 11:10.135
This is Sarah's room.

11:10.137 --> 11:12.037
Wow.

11:12.039 --> 11:15.707
Did she work at a trophy store?

11:15.709 --> 11:18.543
I guess you can start packing
this one up in the morning.

11:18.545 --> 11:20.645
You okay.

11:20.647 --> 11:22.981
I will be.

11:22.983 --> 11:26.317
I know.

11:26.319 --> 11:28.053
Thank you for having me here.

11:28.055 --> 11:30.321
Thank you.

11:30.323 --> 11:32.190
Alright, good night.

11:32.192 --> 11:36.227
I'm here if you
need anything, okay?

11:37.063 --> 11:41.066
[DOOR CLOSES]

11:49.809 --> 11:53.812
[MUSIC]

12:10.830 --> 12:11.930
Good morning.

12:11.932 --> 12:13.231
You're up early.

12:13.233 --> 12:14.733
We have a lot to
do today, so...

12:14.735 --> 12:15.900
Are you hungry?

12:15.902 --> 12:16.901
You want some breakfast,
some coffee...

12:16.903 --> 12:19.070
No, I'm fine.

12:19.072 --> 12:21.606
Okay, actually that's good.

12:21.608 --> 12:23.508
Because I realize that you've
been away so long that we

12:23.510 --> 12:27.512
would probably have
to go get groceries.

12:29.715 --> 12:30.882
I realized last night you guys

12:30.884 --> 12:32.917
probably needed some groceries,

12:32.919 --> 12:35.420
so I brought them.

12:35.422 --> 12:37.088
Okay.

12:37.090 --> 12:38.056
Thank you.

12:38.058 --> 12:39.390
You're welcome.

12:39.392 --> 12:40.792
Nothing was open yet, though.

12:40.794 --> 12:44.095
So I just borrowed what I could
from the church pantry.

12:44.097 --> 12:45.563
That's a lot of mustard.

12:45.565 --> 12:46.898
That's great, though.

12:46.900 --> 12:48.066
Because I was thinking today
that I would love

12:48.068 --> 12:51.035
for breakfast to have a thousand
hot dogs.

12:51.037 --> 12:52.637
That sounds good.

12:52.639 --> 12:55.306
That'll keep.

12:55.308 --> 12:59.344
You know we're
leaving in two weeks?

13:01.113 --> 13:03.281
(WHISPERING) I appreciate
everything you're doing for her.

13:03.283 --> 13:04.783
I really do.

13:04.785 --> 13:08.787
But, moving Naomi to New York?

13:08.789 --> 13:10.555
Its the best thing for her.

13:10.557 --> 13:11.956
Its what she wants to do.

13:11.958 --> 13:13.091
Best thing for her?

13:13.093 --> 13:14.726
Or best thing for you?

13:14.728 --> 13:16.161
She's not going to be living
with me.

13:16.163 --> 13:17.996
She's going to be
living with Chaz.

13:17.998 --> 13:19.397
Exactly.

13:19.399 --> 13:22.167
That's going to last about a
week, at the most.

13:22.169 --> 13:24.335
I'll take care of her.

13:24.337 --> 13:27.071
She's lived here forty years.

13:27.073 --> 13:28.139
We're her family.

13:28.141 --> 13:29.440
You know, let us
take care of her.

13:29.442 --> 13:31.776
Right, you should
take care of her.

13:31.778 --> 13:35.580
By honoring what she has said
she wants to do which is...

13:35.582 --> 13:36.915
Oh, what was it?

13:36.917 --> 13:40.919
Yeah, go to New York.

13:51.597 --> 13:55.600
[MUSIC]

14:13.485 --> 14:17.522
Yes!

14:19.024 --> 14:23.061
[OS] Here you go, hon.

14:23.829 --> 14:24.863
Hello!

14:24.865 --> 14:26.197
Hi.

14:26.199 --> 14:27.799
Yeah, I'm Jessie.

14:27.801 --> 14:28.900
Oh yeah, we know who you are.

14:28.902 --> 14:31.970
Look who it is, everybody!

14:31.972 --> 14:35.640
Oh, hi.

14:35.642 --> 14:37.475
Let's see, can I get a half
caff mocha

14:37.477 --> 14:39.811
with soy and lots
of whip, please.

14:39.813 --> 14:43.514
I'm so sorry, we don't have
your fancy city coffees here.

14:43.516 --> 14:45.583
Oh, that's okay.

14:45.585 --> 14:49.153
Let's do a big coffee, lots of
cream, lots of sugar.

14:49.155 --> 14:53.157
You got it, large coffee...

14:54.927 --> 14:56.361
Hey Daphne, can I get my large

14:56.363 --> 14:58.329
choco-cino with blended whip?

14:58.331 --> 14:59.564
You got it, Shae.

14:59.566 --> 15:03.201
Hey Joe, get Shae's special,
blended whip.

15:03.203 --> 15:05.870
So no fancy city coffees, huh?

15:05.872 --> 15:07.705
Extra cream, extra sugar,
is it?

15:07.707 --> 15:11.743
Alright.

15:12.044 --> 15:15.613
Oh, okay.

15:15.615 --> 15:16.848
When you have a second,

15:16.850 --> 15:17.782
do you think I could talk to
your manager?

15:17.784 --> 15:21.386
No problem!

15:21.388 --> 15:25.423
Hi, I'm the manager, what can I
do for you?

15:26.358 --> 15:28.927
I'm just trying to get a decent
cup of coffee?

15:28.929 --> 15:31.396
I know, um... Fuel depot.

15:31.398 --> 15:34.599
Its about thirty miles
down 86 south.

15:34.601 --> 15:36.434
They make amazing coffee.

15:36.436 --> 15:40.471
Great.

15:41.573 --> 15:43.608
Okay, great.

15:43.610 --> 15:47.645
Thank you.

15:48.414 --> 15:49.914
Cheers.

15:49.916 --> 15:51.082
Head out now,
you won't hit traffic.

15:51.084 --> 15:55.153
Okay.

16:07.299 --> 16:11.336
Okay, preacher.

16:12.004 --> 16:15.773
You following me or is that
just your truck's top speed?

16:15.775 --> 16:17.141
Naomi said you went out.

16:17.143 --> 16:20.178
I thought you might get lost.

16:20.180 --> 16:24.248
You know your downtown is only
five blocks, right?

16:24.250 --> 16:25.783
And all on one
side of the street.

16:25.785 --> 16:29.354
Yeah, there is more to Bethel
Cove than you might think.

16:29.356 --> 16:31.322
Why don't you hop in and

16:31.324 --> 16:34.158
I'll give you a tour?

16:34.160 --> 16:36.461
I don't have time, lot of
packing to do still.

16:36.463 --> 16:38.496
And it's taking me a little bit
longer to do what with all

16:38.498 --> 16:42.166
of the tape that disappeared.

16:42.168 --> 16:46.237
Yeah, sorry, that was...

16:46.939 --> 16:48.539
Stupid?

16:48.541 --> 16:49.874
Let me make it up to you?

16:49.876 --> 16:53.911
Give you a ride back?

16:54.513 --> 16:56.547
Yeah, yes.

16:56.549 --> 16:57.782
I'll take a ride back.

16:57.784 --> 16:59.984
Thank you.

16:59.986 --> 17:03.521
Wow, quite the chariot here.

17:03.523 --> 17:04.288
That's a lot of tape.

17:04.290 --> 17:05.656
It is, it is.

17:05.657 --> 17:06.958
If you want to use any of it to
fix up your truck,

17:06.960 --> 17:08.526
by all means.

17:08.528 --> 17:10.461
I'm pretty good, actually, I
have some leftover.

17:10.463 --> 17:14.065
You do?

17:14.067 --> 17:17.234
So, is this how you usually
pick up women?

17:17.237 --> 17:18.569
What?!

17:18.570 --> 17:21.339
No, no, I didn't...

17:21.340 --> 17:23.540
That was a joke.

17:23.542 --> 17:25.977
Ben, that was just a joke.

17:25.979 --> 17:27.979
Sheesh, totally
worth it, though.

17:27.981 --> 17:31.149
[LAUGHING]

17:31.151 --> 17:32.850
Naomi was that way.

17:32.852 --> 17:34.185
Yeah, I know, but I'm going to
take you

17:34.187 --> 17:35.486
to see the museum first.

17:35.488 --> 17:36.387
It's great.

17:36.389 --> 17:37.188
The museum?

17:37.190 --> 17:38.556
Yeah.

17:38.558 --> 17:41.059
As enticing of an offer as a
museum day sounds,

17:41.061 --> 17:43.861
I really do have a ton of stuff
to do.

17:43.863 --> 17:47.899
That woman has been holding on
to stuff for years...

17:49.835 --> 17:53.838
Okay, you're starting to creep
me out here, tapeworm.

17:55.674 --> 17:59.177
Allright.

17:59.179 --> 18:00.878
Here's the deal.

18:00.880 --> 18:04.916
Naomi has company coming over.

18:06.752 --> 18:10.788
Her friends want to talk to her
about staying here.

18:11.423 --> 18:12.590
In her home.

18:12.592 --> 18:13.958
Honestly, I am totally fine
with that,

18:13.960 --> 18:15.626
but I should at least be there.

18:15.628 --> 18:17.962
These are friends from church.

18:17.964 --> 18:20.698
Right.

18:20.700 --> 18:24.702
Oh, you think I'm going to
embarrass her?

18:25.037 --> 18:26.270
You have to understand, Jessie,

18:26.272 --> 18:30.308
Chaz tends to attract a certain
type of woman.

18:30.943 --> 18:32.410
That didn't come out right.

18:32.412 --> 18:36.481
No, I think that came out just
perfectly, Ben.

18:36.648 --> 18:39.617
I completely understand.

18:39.619 --> 18:41.319
But, I don't think
you should worry.

18:41.321 --> 18:43.454
I'm probably not going to make
it to the meeting on time

18:43.456 --> 18:45.490
because its really time
consuming to just wander around

18:45.492 --> 18:47.925
a neighborhood and try to find
someone to sleep with.

18:47.927 --> 18:51.963
[DOOR SLAMS]

19:01.740 --> 19:03.174
Are you sure about leaving?

19:03.176 --> 19:04.675
This community needs you.

19:04.677 --> 19:06.577
We've saved your seat on the
committee, kept it open.

19:06.579 --> 19:08.279
[DOOR OPENS]

19:08.281 --> 19:09.514
Hi!

19:09.516 --> 19:11.949
Jessie, this is Doris Sheeline,
Melinda Alders,

19:11.951 --> 19:13.584
and Elaine Crowley.

19:13.586 --> 19:14.919
And Eddie.

19:14.921 --> 19:17.755
Hello, I'm Jessie.

19:17.757 --> 19:19.757
Naomi's daughter-in-law.

19:19.759 --> 19:22.960
Well, ex
daughter-in-law, really.

19:22.962 --> 19:24.962
I divorced her son.

19:24.964 --> 19:26.964
That was a lot of information,
wasn't it?

19:26.966 --> 19:29.433
And it sounded bad, but its not
bad, its good.

19:29.435 --> 19:31.169
Its, so good!

19:31.171 --> 19:33.604
Cause he was the worst.

19:33.606 --> 19:35.606
Not the worst.

19:35.608 --> 19:38.476
You raised him to have many
fine qualities.

19:38.478 --> 19:42.513
Just none of them that were
visited upon me consistently,

19:42.881 --> 19:44.949
so in this case its great.

19:44.951 --> 19:45.883
Good divorce!

19:45.885 --> 19:48.319
Thank God-

19:48.321 --> 19:51.222
Goodness, thank goodness
we divorced

19:51.224 --> 19:52.723
because its better now.

19:52.725 --> 19:56.627
Life is better for me now.

19:56.629 --> 19:57.995
I'm going to start again.

19:57.997 --> 19:59.664
I'm Jessie!

19:59.666 --> 20:01.632
I like her.

20:01.634 --> 20:02.900
Oh.

20:02.902 --> 20:06.938
[TRAFFIC]

20:09.208 --> 20:10.975
[GLASS BREAKS]

20:10.977 --> 20:14.345
Naomi, are you okay?

20:14.347 --> 20:18.082
[OS] In here.

20:18.084 --> 20:19.817
Hey!

20:19.819 --> 20:21.319
Oh.

20:21.321 --> 20:22.820
What happened?

20:22.822 --> 20:26.891
I was clumsy, that's all.

20:28.393 --> 20:30.728
Do you think maybe we're moving
a little too fast here?

20:30.730 --> 20:32.230
It is Sunday, you want to take
a day off

20:32.232 --> 20:33.397
and go do something fun?

20:33.399 --> 20:36.067
Oh no, I got enough rest.

20:36.069 --> 20:37.501
Lets just keep moving, okay?

20:37.503 --> 20:38.502
Keep packing.

20:38.504 --> 20:39.403
You sure?

20:39.405 --> 20:42.573
Yeah, I'm sure.

20:42.575 --> 20:46.644
Okay.

20:59.124 --> 21:03.160
[MUSIC]

21:15.107 --> 21:16.707
I have an idea.

21:16.709 --> 21:19.143
Lets go church-ing.

21:19.145 --> 21:21.145
No, not a verb.

21:21.147 --> 21:22.580
I still think we should go.

21:22.582 --> 21:25.216
You've been asking me to go for
years, today's the day.

21:25.218 --> 21:27.218
Maybe you should just go?

21:27.220 --> 21:28.919
No, I'm not going
to church alone,

21:28.921 --> 21:31.455
they'll burn me at the stake.

21:31.457 --> 21:34.558
I don't think so, Jessie, I'm
just not up for it.

21:34.560 --> 21:35.993
You're right.

21:35.995 --> 21:40.031
Who needs church?

21:40.766 --> 21:44.802
[LAUGHING] Alright, lets
go church-ing.

21:45.304 --> 21:46.337
Yes?

21:46.339 --> 21:50.374
Yes, oh yeah.

21:50.742 --> 21:53.344
[CHURCH BELLS]

21:53.346 --> 21:55.279
Dear brothers and sisters,

21:55.281 --> 21:58.082
when troubles of any kind come
your way,

21:58.084 --> 22:02.153
consider it a gift coming down
to us from God our Father.

22:02.321 --> 22:05.756
I'm sorry, did he just say your
troubles are a gift?

22:05.758 --> 22:08.459
I'm sorry, I didn't hear.

22:08.461 --> 22:09.627
[SERMON CONTINUES] ...with a
divided loyalty

22:09.629 --> 22:13.531
is as unsettled to as
God our Father...

22:14.766 --> 22:18.769
Excuse me, Ben...
or, your holiness?

22:19.204 --> 22:21.772
Ben's fine.

22:21.774 --> 22:23.174
Or pastor.

22:23.176 --> 22:25.209
You just said that our troubles
are gifts

22:25.211 --> 22:29.246
and if that's true, I've got
some gifts coming to me.

22:29.681 --> 22:32.550
That's not actually
what I was...

22:32.552 --> 22:36.587
Let me just go back...

22:43.462 --> 22:46.297
I think you're right.

22:46.299 --> 22:49.633
The verse should read, "When
troubles of any kind

22:49.635 --> 22:53.637
come your way, consider it an
opportunity for great joy,

22:54.373 --> 22:56.574
for you know that when your
faith is tested,

22:56.576 --> 22:58.843
your endurance has a
chance to grow...

22:58.845 --> 23:01.078
Sorry, jumping in again.

23:01.080 --> 23:03.914
You just said that our troubles
are joy,

23:03.916 --> 23:06.684
which is ridiculous.

23:06.686 --> 23:09.420
No, that's right.

23:09.422 --> 23:11.021
James I.

23:11.023 --> 23:13.090
What did James win?

23:13.092 --> 23:15.192
Its in the bible.

23:15.194 --> 23:16.660
Right.

23:16.662 --> 23:18.696
Okay, here's the thing.

23:18.698 --> 23:21.365
Its actually kind of a
beautiful meaning if-

23:21.367 --> 23:25.102
[DORIS CLEARS HER THROAT]

23:25.104 --> 23:27.538
You know what, we don't
generally ask questions

23:27.540 --> 23:29.573
during the sermon, sorry.

23:29.575 --> 23:32.176
Oh, sorry.

23:32.178 --> 23:33.577
Sorry.

23:33.579 --> 23:37.615
Of course you don't.

23:38.550 --> 23:42.686
Its alright.

23:42.688 --> 23:43.687
Where was I?

23:43.689 --> 23:45.222
That's a question.

23:45.224 --> 23:46.056
Is it?

23:46.058 --> 23:48.726
Also a question.

23:48.728 --> 23:50.094
You know what?

23:50.096 --> 23:52.797
We were almost near the end
anyways, so lets sing.

23:52.799 --> 23:56.834
Hymn number four
hundred,please.

24:00.972 --> 24:05.009
[BAD SINGING]

24:08.880 --> 24:12.883
Is it supposed to be this bad?

24:14.920 --> 24:18.088
I don't think its really that
bad, I mean...

24:18.090 --> 24:19.223
Yeah no, its pretty bad.

24:19.225 --> 24:21.992
This is Lyle's favorite song.

24:21.994 --> 24:23.494
Really?

24:23.496 --> 24:27.531
This was?

24:33.472 --> 24:35.840
Discipline is a virtue.

24:35.842 --> 24:37.675
You didn't make it
through the sermon.

24:37.677 --> 24:39.977
Well, Doris, I had a
bit of a distraction.

24:39.979 --> 24:42.313
Hence, discipline.

24:42.315 --> 24:46.350
We can't afford to lose any
more attendees.

24:51.089 --> 24:52.656
Its good to see you.

24:52.658 --> 24:56.694
Its always good to see you.

25:00.499 --> 25:02.032
Wow.

25:02.034 --> 25:03.300
That was-

25:03.302 --> 25:05.202
Your first time in a church,
I'm guessing.

25:05.204 --> 25:06.937
Mm-hmm.

25:06.939 --> 25:10.274
So, what did you think?

25:10.276 --> 25:14.278
I thought it was interesting.

25:15.847 --> 25:19.884
Yeah, I didn't
love it, honestly.

25:20.352 --> 25:22.052
Not because of you.

25:22.054 --> 25:26.090
I just don't know if I'm really
a church person.

25:26.391 --> 25:28.626
But, we got Mom
out of the house.

25:28.628 --> 25:31.729
Yeah, actually I wanted to
thank you for getting her out.

25:31.731 --> 25:32.796
She needs that.

25:32.798 --> 25:33.697
You're very welcome.

25:33.699 --> 25:37.735
And I kind of think that she-

25:37.903 --> 25:39.904
Where is she going?

25:39.906 --> 25:43.941
I think I know where.

25:44.676 --> 25:48.712
[MUSIC]

25:55.320 --> 25:59.356
[SIGHING] I think you're right.

25:59.358 --> 26:03.394
She's not ready, I'm pushing
her too fast.

26:04.529 --> 26:08.566
Listen, why don't we just worry
about helping her?

26:11.603 --> 26:15.639
Together.

26:15.941 --> 26:19.977
[CHURCH BELLS]

26:28.753 --> 26:30.387
Oh.

26:30.389 --> 26:31.288
No, it's okay.

26:31.290 --> 26:32.289
No, I want to.

26:32.291 --> 26:33.457
I want to.

26:33.459 --> 26:34.758
Okay.

26:34.760 --> 26:35.859
Well, no, that's a lot.

26:35.861 --> 26:36.760
That's a little extreme.

26:36.762 --> 26:38.462
Let's do $25?

26:38.464 --> 26:39.730
$20?

26:39.732 --> 26:41.532
[THROAT CLEARING]

26:41.534 --> 26:44.268
No, yeah, I don't need change.

26:44.270 --> 26:45.035
Thank you.

26:45.037 --> 26:47.605
You're welcome.

26:47.607 --> 26:50.374
That was a lot.

26:50.376 --> 26:51.475
They're going to do well today.

26:51.477 --> 26:53.544
There are a lot of people here.

26:53.546 --> 26:56.113
You should have seen what it
was like years ago when

26:56.115 --> 26:58.816
so many people used to come here
to hear Ben talk.

26:58.818 --> 27:01.819
When he first came here, fresh
out of the seminary,

27:01.821 --> 27:05.289
so young and so inspired.

27:05.291 --> 27:09.293
It's what made Sarah fall in
love with him.

27:09.561 --> 27:10.894
Good morning.

27:10.896 --> 27:12.296
[AUDIENCE] Good morning.

27:12.298 --> 27:14.498
It's good to see
some old friends.

27:14.500 --> 27:16.500
Even some new ones.

27:16.502 --> 27:18.235
Today's sermon is on-

27:18.237 --> 27:19.570
Oh, hey!

27:19.572 --> 27:21.305
Ben, I wanted to...

27:21.307 --> 27:23.774
Don't worry, I promise I'm not
going to interrupt today-

27:23.776 --> 27:24.675
And yet?

27:24.677 --> 27:26.844
And yet, hold on,

27:26.846 --> 27:28.646
I thought I would just go ahead
and ask my questions

27:28.648 --> 27:32.683
at the top before you get to the
notecard thing.

27:33.318 --> 27:34.918
How thoughtful of you.

27:34.920 --> 27:38.022
So, how do you know if this is
the one true religion and, if it

27:38.024 --> 27:42.059
is, does it mean that all of the
other religions are wrong?

27:42.594 --> 27:44.862
Oh good, an easy one.

27:44.864 --> 27:47.297
That was way less
boring this time.

27:47.299 --> 27:48.265
That's our new slogan.

27:48.267 --> 27:49.133
Is it?!

27:49.135 --> 27:49.867
Yeah.

27:49.869 --> 27:51.001
I like that.

27:51.003 --> 27:51.769
I do expect some
royalties, though.

27:51.771 --> 27:53.137
Absolutely.

27:53.139 --> 27:55.806
She was actually singing today.

27:55.808 --> 27:57.207
It was very sweet.

27:57.209 --> 27:58.542
So nicely done.

27:58.544 --> 28:00.477
You want to double down and
take her to lunch?

28:00.479 --> 28:01.712
Yeah-

28:01.714 --> 28:02.880
Excuse me, pastor, the
committee would like to

28:02.882 --> 28:04.982
have a word with you today
before you go.

28:04.984 --> 28:07.117
Of course.

28:07.119 --> 28:09.153
I'll meet you both
at the diner after.

28:09.155 --> 28:10.721
Yes, it's a date.

28:10.723 --> 28:12.523
No, it's not a date.

28:12.525 --> 28:14.224
It's not a date.

28:14.226 --> 28:17.394
It's just the pastor going out
with two women.

28:17.396 --> 28:18.829
So much better.

28:18.831 --> 28:20.364
Yeah, it sounded like it was
going to be in my head

28:20.366 --> 28:21.799
before I said it.

28:21.801 --> 28:22.900
I'm going to go get Mom.

28:22.902 --> 28:24.234
Twice now you've
allowed this woman

28:24.236 --> 28:26.537
to disrupt our services.

28:26.539 --> 28:28.839
What's wrong with a little
spice in our services?

28:28.841 --> 28:30.674
What would you
have me do, Doris?

28:30.676 --> 28:32.743
Uninvite her to church?

28:32.745 --> 28:36.413
You can't sacrifice an entire
congregation for one person.

28:36.415 --> 28:37.748
You're right.

28:37.750 --> 28:40.851
Heaven forbid we promote
sacrifice in church.

28:40.853 --> 28:44.021
Sorry.

28:44.023 --> 28:45.355
I'll talk to her.

28:45.357 --> 28:46.990
Excellent.

28:46.992 --> 28:49.893
Now let's talk about next
Sunday's lessons.

28:49.895 --> 28:53.931
simplesermonsweekly.com has a
lovely one on discipline.

28:54.532 --> 28:58.569
Great.

29:00.105 --> 29:01.371
There you go.

29:01.373 --> 29:02.873
That's the way I like it.

29:02.875 --> 29:05.242
You know, Daphne, I am going to
win you over

29:05.244 --> 29:06.877
whether you like it or not.

29:06.879 --> 29:08.846
No, but you keep trying.

29:08.848 --> 29:10.514
I will, I will!

29:10.516 --> 29:14.518
I'm very tenacious!

29:15.019 --> 29:15.753
Hey!

29:15.755 --> 29:17.454
Hey, how was Doris?

29:17.456 --> 29:19.556
Oh, she's great.

29:19.558 --> 29:21.692
Big fan of yours, by the way.

29:21.694 --> 29:23.260
I thought she might be.

29:23.262 --> 29:24.294
Here you go sweetie.

29:24.296 --> 29:25.462
Thanks.

29:25.464 --> 29:29.233
Oh, you got a menu,
how lovely for you.

29:29.235 --> 29:30.200
Thank you.

29:30.202 --> 29:31.401
Where's Naomi?

29:31.403 --> 29:34.037
She left immediately
after the service.

29:34.039 --> 29:35.272
I think the only way we're
getting her out of the house

29:35.274 --> 29:37.241
is when she thinks she's going
to convert me.

29:37.243 --> 29:39.810
Kind of a shame that church is
only on Sundays.

29:39.812 --> 29:41.078
That's it.

29:41.080 --> 29:42.446
No, seriously.

29:42.448 --> 29:43.981
Ask her if she'll host a bible
study at her house

29:43.983 --> 29:44.948
during the week.

29:44.950 --> 29:46.416
She'd never say no to that.

29:46.418 --> 29:48.585
She would never believe that.

29:48.587 --> 29:50.721
Like a bunch of people are just
going to get together

29:50.723 --> 29:54.725
at a house and study the bible.

29:55.326 --> 29:56.160
Is that a real thing?

29:56.162 --> 29:57.828
Yeah.

29:57.830 --> 29:58.962
Well, just in this town?

29:58.964 --> 30:02.733
Worldwide.

30:02.735 --> 30:04.802
Hey Chazzi.

30:04.804 --> 30:08.605
Well, you're not going to
believe this but,

30:08.607 --> 30:12.643
Jessie and Ben are getting
awful friendly.

30:16.848 --> 30:17.981
You've gone too far.

30:17.983 --> 30:20.184
You've gone to
third Corinthians.

30:20.186 --> 30:22.986
[LAUGHTER]

30:22.988 --> 30:25.522
Okay, I have a Job question.

30:25.524 --> 30:26.790
[PRONOUNCES IT LIKE
JOB / OCCUPATION]

30:26.792 --> 30:28.859
So, Job's entire family is
wiped out,

30:28.861 --> 30:32.930
and I'm just confused why him
getting new kids

30:32.932 --> 30:34.598
would make that okay.

30:34.600 --> 30:36.800
It's Job. [PRONOUNCES IT WITH A
LONG "O" SOUND]

30:36.802 --> 30:40.137
No, in mine it's job.

30:40.139 --> 30:43.173
[PHONE RINGING]

30:43.175 --> 30:44.508
Hey sweetie!

30:44.510 --> 30:46.977
Hey Mom, you sound good.

30:46.979 --> 30:48.212
Well, I'm just very
excited to be

30:48.214 --> 30:50.280
moving in with my new roomie.

30:50.282 --> 30:54.284
That's great, so you're all
packed up then?

30:54.619 --> 30:57.287
Well, it's taking a little bit
longer than I expected.

30:57.289 --> 31:00.557
Mom, the moving truck's will be
there in less than a week.

31:00.559 --> 31:02.392
Can't we postpone them?

31:02.394 --> 31:04.161
I just need a little
bit more time.

31:04.163 --> 31:06.029
No, Mom, we can't.

31:06.031 --> 31:07.297
How's Jessie doing?

31:07.299 --> 31:09.032
Is she helping you or slowing
things down?

31:09.034 --> 31:10.300
I know she means well.

31:10.302 --> 31:13.804
[JESSIE TALKING & LAUGHING IN
THE BACKGROUND]

31:13.806 --> 31:15.505
Is that Jessie?

31:15.507 --> 31:16.240
What's that?

31:16.242 --> 31:18.175
Mom?

31:18.177 --> 31:22.246
You know what, I'm going to
call you back.

31:23.514 --> 31:25.148
[ON PHONE] Hardball, what's
going on?

31:25.150 --> 31:26.917
Hey Jim, what's up, buddy?

31:26.919 --> 31:28.552
Just want to let you know that
everything's going good,

31:28.554 --> 31:30.821
but the homeowner might need a
couple more weeks

31:30.823 --> 31:32.356
to move out.

31:32.358 --> 31:33.991
If that's possible.

31:33.993 --> 31:35.492
If we can't start demolition on
the first,

31:35.494 --> 31:37.427
I've got to go with
the other location.

31:37.429 --> 31:41.064
10 days, Ellison.

31:41.066 --> 31:44.935
You know, I could get used to
this "churching".

31:44.937 --> 31:46.603
Those were really
important questions.

31:46.605 --> 31:50.374
I just never really thought to
ask them before.

31:50.376 --> 31:51.775
You know, it's still
a little early.

31:51.777 --> 31:53.043
Do you want to
do something fun?

31:53.045 --> 31:54.077
No.

31:54.079 --> 31:56.046
Wait.

31:56.048 --> 31:58.882
Yes, do you want to
go see a movie?

31:58.884 --> 31:59.950
Some other evening.

31:59.952 --> 32:02.185
No, it's "Charade", Mom.

32:02.187 --> 32:03.253
I want to go see "Charade".

32:03.255 --> 32:04.421
I've seen it.

32:04.423 --> 32:06.056
Okay, you haven't
seen it with me.

32:06.058 --> 32:07.925
Come on, it starts in thirty
minutes, let's go.

32:07.927 --> 32:10.060
Why don't you go in line, get
us tickets,

32:10.062 --> 32:11.895
and I'll just meet you there
after I finish.

32:11.897 --> 32:14.298
Okay, you're not going to bail
on me, are you?

32:14.300 --> 32:16.533
No, I promise you won't have to
see the movie alone.

32:16.535 --> 32:17.768
No, go, hurry.

32:17.770 --> 32:18.869
Okay.

32:18.871 --> 32:22.940
[MUSIC]

32:27.045 --> 32:27.711
Hey pastor.

32:27.713 --> 32:31.782
Hey guys.

32:34.485 --> 32:36.253
Hey!

32:36.255 --> 32:37.921
Hey, pastor Ben!

32:37.923 --> 32:38.922
Where's Naomi?

32:38.924 --> 32:40.824
She told me to meet her here.

32:40.826 --> 32:42.092
She's not here yet.

32:42.094 --> 32:45.329
She sent me down here to get a
spot in line.

32:45.331 --> 32:47.331
There's never a line here,
is there?

32:47.333 --> 32:49.466
Not ever, no.

32:49.468 --> 32:52.569
Great.

32:52.571 --> 32:53.770
Did she set us up?

32:53.772 --> 32:55.472
What?

32:55.474 --> 32:56.406
No!

32:56.408 --> 32:57.774
Yeah, no!

32:57.776 --> 33:01.812
No, it's stilly.

33:05.283 --> 33:06.583
It's a shame, though.

33:06.585 --> 33:08.251
I was looking forward to seeing
this one.

33:08.253 --> 33:10.487
You've never seen charade?

33:10.489 --> 33:13.757
Hepburn, Grant, mystery comedy.

33:13.759 --> 33:15.092
No.

33:15.094 --> 33:16.693
All right, we are seeing it
right now, come on.

33:16.695 --> 33:18.662
You're going to get it
in a second.

33:18.664 --> 33:20.364
Hi.

33:20.366 --> 33:21.264
Pastor!

33:21.266 --> 33:22.165
Hi!

33:22.167 --> 33:24.968
Pastor Kingston.

33:24.970 --> 33:26.837
I'll take this one, Evon.

33:26.839 --> 33:28.005
Two please.

33:28.007 --> 33:28.972
I got mine.

33:28.974 --> 33:30.874
No, they're $2.50 each.

33:30.876 --> 33:32.209
I'll treat.

33:32.211 --> 33:34.344
Okay, just don't think that I'm
sleeping with you

33:34.346 --> 33:36.713
because you're paying.

33:36.715 --> 33:39.016
She's kidding, we're not-

33:39.018 --> 33:40.951
I don't put out for $2.50.

33:40.953 --> 33:42.452
Right, Doris?

33:42.454 --> 33:46.123
But, you spring for popcorn,
and we'll talk about it.

33:46.858 --> 33:48.792
[FROM HEPBURN ON MOVIE SCREEN]
"You're blocking my view."

33:48.794 --> 33:50.460
"Which view would you prefer?"

33:50.462 --> 33:51.661
"The one you're blocking."

33:51.663 --> 33:52.496
"What's your name?"

33:52.498 --> 33:53.797
"Peter Joshua."

33:53.799 --> 33:54.965
"Mine's Regina Lampert."

33:54.967 --> 33:55.999
"Is there a Mr. Lampert?"

33:56.001 --> 33:56.666
"Yes."

33:56.668 --> 33:57.734
"Good for you."

33:57.736 --> 34:01.204
"No, it isn't,
I'm getting a divorce."

34:01.206 --> 34:03.373
Pastor?

34:03.375 --> 34:04.307
Doris?

34:04.309 --> 34:06.043
Everything okay?

34:06.045 --> 34:10.047
We're fine, thank you.

34:12.250 --> 34:14.184
[LAUGHING]

34:14.186 --> 34:15.318
This is going to be fun.

34:15.320 --> 34:19.322
Don't, please don't.

34:29.033 --> 34:33.003
Wait for it.

34:34.906 --> 34:36.206
You know I'm going to pay for
this later.

34:36.208 --> 34:36.907
I'm sorry.

34:36.909 --> 34:37.607
You're not sorry.

34:37.609 --> 34:39.042
Not even remotely, no.

34:39.043 --> 34:43.080
That's what I thought.

34:43.281 --> 34:45.681
[LAUGHING]

34:45.684 --> 34:47.751
That was so awesome!

34:47.753 --> 34:50.187
Yeah, amazing for you.

34:50.188 --> 34:51.221
She doesn't run the committee

34:51.223 --> 34:52.889
that holds your job
in the balance.

34:52.891 --> 34:54.690
I think it's pronounced Job.
[SHE SAYS WITH LONG "O" SOUND]

34:54.693 --> 34:55.958
Cute.

34:55.960 --> 34:59.996
Thank you.

35:01.299 --> 35:03.700
Come on, I'll walk you home.

35:03.702 --> 35:05.735
I'll walk you home.

35:05.737 --> 35:07.304
I assume you have a home, yes?

35:07.306 --> 35:08.939
- Yes.
- Good.

35:08.941 --> 35:12.309
Technically it's a room in the
back of a church but, yes.

35:12.311 --> 35:13.076
The commute's great.

35:13.078 --> 35:13.910
Is it?

35:13.912 --> 35:16.379
Yes.

35:16.381 --> 35:19.149
Well, it was half
a degree, actually.

35:19.151 --> 35:21.551
Early childhood education.

35:21.553 --> 35:25.555
I had about a year to go and I
met Chaz and he was older

35:26.591 --> 35:30.627
and successful and I really
wanted to have a family.

35:32.263 --> 35:35.899
You went with Chaz
for stability?

35:35.901 --> 35:38.668
Ha.

35:38.670 --> 35:40.971
Chaz was different then.

35:40.973 --> 35:43.507
It's hard to believe
but he was.

35:43.509 --> 35:46.643
Plus his parents were perfect
role models.

35:46.645 --> 35:49.412
Yeah, they are.

35:49.414 --> 35:51.281
They really took to you.

35:51.283 --> 35:55.318
Naomi especially.

35:56.320 --> 35:57.287
Was that rain?

35:57.289 --> 35:58.321
No.

35:58.323 --> 35:59.422
No?

35:59.424 --> 36:00.790
I think it was.

36:00.792 --> 36:03.026
Okay, come on, I've
got a shortcut.

36:03.028 --> 36:06.329
[THUNDER IN THE DISTANCE]

36:06.331 --> 36:08.165
Shortcut through a cemetery.

36:08.167 --> 36:10.534
This is not creepy at all.

36:10.536 --> 36:12.302
Cemeteries are great.

36:12.304 --> 36:13.837
People are dying
to get in here.

36:13.839 --> 36:16.173
[LAUGHTER]

36:16.175 --> 36:17.541
Somebody's going to have to
teach you

36:17.543 --> 36:19.643
the basic concepts of humor.

36:19.645 --> 36:22.379
Oh yeah, I guess I can admit
you seem...

36:22.381 --> 36:24.014
Kind of funny.

36:24.016 --> 36:26.283
Oh, thanks.

36:26.285 --> 36:29.719
Where did you get that from,
your parents?

36:29.721 --> 36:33.723
Well, I have no idea if my Dad
was funny and I think

36:34.458 --> 36:36.793
probably the only joke in my
Mom's life was having a kid

36:36.795 --> 36:40.797
that she wasn't ready for, so-

36:41.465 --> 36:45.468
I did not know that parents
like Naomi and Lyle existed.

36:46.370 --> 36:48.205
You know, they told
me a little,

36:48.207 --> 36:52.242
but can I ask how you handled
losing Sarah?

36:54.045 --> 36:58.148
It's just finding a routine and
sticking to it.

36:58.150 --> 36:59.316
Oh, the pastor routine?

36:59.318 --> 37:02.219
The pastor routine, yes.

37:02.221 --> 37:05.322
So you didn't stop
believing in God?

37:05.324 --> 37:06.590
Nope.

37:06.592 --> 37:10.026
Can't be mad at someone you
don't believe in.

37:10.028 --> 37:11.595
You're mad?

37:11.597 --> 37:15.432
You're the calmest mad person
I've ever seen.

37:15.434 --> 37:16.666
People know when I'm mad.

37:16.668 --> 37:18.235
There's a lot of yelling.

37:18.237 --> 37:20.370
Yeah, I can see that, I would
imagine so.

37:20.372 --> 37:22.172
Can you?

37:22.174 --> 37:23.673
So you never yell?

37:23.675 --> 37:27.677
No, we're way past yelling.

37:29.247 --> 37:31.915
With Sarah, I...

37:31.917 --> 37:35.518
I asked Him for a lot.

37:35.520 --> 37:39.522
When she got sick,
we asked for a cure.

37:40.024 --> 37:44.027
When she got really sick,
we asked for more time.

37:47.131 --> 37:50.133
And then at the end,

37:50.135 --> 37:54.104
I just asked that
she wouldn't suffer.

37:54.106 --> 37:55.939
We didn't get any of it.

37:55.941 --> 37:59.976
So, I don't ask anymore.

38:04.582 --> 38:06.950
You have to stop,
I didn't recognize you,

38:06.952 --> 38:08.551
I didn't know you.

38:08.553 --> 38:10.654
Okay, so you only push people
you don't know

38:10.656 --> 38:11.988
into open graves.

38:11.990 --> 38:14.257
Yes, that's exactly what I do.

38:14.259 --> 38:16.660
You're lucky I forgive
very quickly.

38:16.662 --> 38:20.230
Says the guy who gives God the
silent treatment.

38:20.232 --> 38:23.166
No, I talk to God all the time.

38:23.168 --> 38:27.203
I just don't ask him for
anything for myself anymore.

38:28.472 --> 38:31.441
Oh, that's very
altruistic of you.

38:31.443 --> 38:32.409
Thank you.

38:32.411 --> 38:33.243
You ask for other people?

38:33.245 --> 38:34.911
Yeah.

38:34.913 --> 38:36.079
Do you ever ask for me?

38:36.081 --> 38:37.180
You?

38:37.182 --> 38:39.082
I pray for you all the time.

38:39.084 --> 38:41.584
You pray for me all the time?

38:41.586 --> 38:43.787
Yeah.

38:43.789 --> 38:47.324
What do you pray for?

38:47.326 --> 38:50.660
I pray that you find what
you're looking for.

38:50.662 --> 38:54.664
Pray that you find happiness.

38:55.466 --> 38:59.636
What does that sound like or
how do you do it?

38:59.638 --> 39:00.603
How?

39:00.605 --> 39:03.440
Yeah, I mean,

39:03.442 --> 39:05.208
would you do it?

39:05.210 --> 39:06.176
Right now?

39:06.178 --> 39:08.011
Yeah, I mean is that weird?

39:08.013 --> 39:10.513
No, that's not weird at all.

39:10.515 --> 39:12.649
I'll pray for you.

39:12.651 --> 39:14.150
Okay.

39:14.152 --> 39:15.485
You ready?

39:15.487 --> 39:19.522
Yes, well, no.

39:19.857 --> 39:20.690
Ready?

39:20.692 --> 39:22.058
I'm nervous.

39:22.060 --> 39:23.626
It's okay.

39:23.628 --> 39:25.528
Here.

39:25.530 --> 39:29.566
[MUSIC]

39:34.038 --> 39:35.672
Heavenly Father,

39:35.674 --> 39:38.742
We thank you for Jessie.

39:38.744 --> 39:41.711
We thank you for her questions.

39:41.713 --> 39:45.014
We hope you help her
find the answers.

39:45.016 --> 39:48.985
We hope you help her find you.

39:49.420 --> 39:52.322
A-men.

39:52.324 --> 39:56.326
A-men.

39:58.529 --> 40:01.331
So now what?

40:01.333 --> 40:05.335
Now we give him a chance to
talk back.

40:06.103 --> 40:10.006
Does he sound even remotely
like Morgan Freeman?

40:10.008 --> 40:13.977
[LAUGHTER]

40:20.117 --> 40:22.085
So?

40:22.087 --> 40:24.521
So.

40:24.523 --> 40:28.591
I will see you later.

40:31.228 --> 40:35.265
You don't want to thank me for
a great first non-date?

40:38.702 --> 40:40.770
Thank you.

40:40.772 --> 40:44.774
You're welcome.

40:46.710 --> 40:50.713
That was really bad aim.

41:00.791 --> 41:03.560
That was not bad for a pastor.

41:03.562 --> 41:07.530
That was pretty tame for a
heathen, though.

41:08.599 --> 41:10.166
We can't.

41:10.168 --> 41:14.204
Okay.

41:14.572 --> 41:16.406
I'm a pastor.

41:16.408 --> 41:20.410
Right, okay.

41:21.579 --> 41:24.581
Woah!

41:24.583 --> 41:26.316
Are you okay?

41:26.318 --> 41:28.117
All good.

41:28.119 --> 41:31.120
[LAUGHTER]

41:31.122 --> 41:35.158
I...

41:37.361 --> 41:39.429
- Good night.
- Good night!

41:45.002 --> 41:48.938
Good night!

41:48.940 --> 41:52.442
Ben, you're not going to take
your truck?

41:52.444 --> 41:54.177
I'll get it later.

41:54.179 --> 41:58.214
[MUSIC SWELLS]

42:22.640 --> 42:24.474
[CRASHING SOUND]

42:24.476 --> 42:27.343
Mom?

42:27.345 --> 42:28.211
Naomi?

42:28.213 --> 42:31.314
Hey.

42:31.316 --> 42:32.348
Hey!

42:32.350 --> 42:35.218
Is it safe?

42:35.220 --> 42:38.254
Who's bright idea was it to put
weights in the attic?

42:38.256 --> 42:39.856
I'm going to guess a man.

42:39.858 --> 42:42.225
Yeah, who's not here to help me
box them up.

42:42.227 --> 42:46.262
Thank you, Charlie.

42:47.364 --> 42:49.832
So?

42:49.834 --> 42:52.001
How was the movie?

42:52.003 --> 42:55.605
It was okay.

42:55.607 --> 42:57.874
Just okay?

42:57.876 --> 43:00.577
Yeah, you know.

43:00.579 --> 43:04.614
Big screen, popcorn.

43:05.849 --> 43:07.383
So it was great?

43:07.385 --> 43:11.421
It was great, yeah.

43:12.423 --> 43:16.092
Wow, Mom, looking around,

43:16.094 --> 43:18.728
there's still a lot of stuff we
still have to pack.

43:18.730 --> 43:20.263
I know.

43:20.265 --> 43:21.931
I wonder if it's going to take
us just a little bit longer

43:21.933 --> 43:23.433
to pack than we
initially thought?

43:23.435 --> 43:24.634
You think?

43:24.636 --> 43:26.102
I do.

43:26.104 --> 43:28.938
I feel like maybe we should get
used to the idea

43:28.940 --> 43:32.642
of being in Bethel Cove
a little longer?

43:32.644 --> 43:34.410
Maybe we should?

43:34.412 --> 43:38.481
Maybe we should.

43:41.819 --> 43:43.119
But you still have
to help me pack.

43:43.121 --> 43:47.156
Yes, yes, I should
be helping you.

43:47.591 --> 43:51.628
[CHURCH BELLS]

43:59.837 --> 44:02.105
We're going to have to get here
earlier next time.

44:02.107 --> 44:03.573
Well...

44:03.575 --> 44:06.609
- Hi.
- Hi.

44:06.611 --> 44:10.580
Okay, I'm going to go
find us a seat.

44:11.015 --> 44:15.051
I'll join you.

44:16.086 --> 44:17.920
You look nice.

44:17.922 --> 44:20.657
You look pretty nice, too.

44:20.659 --> 44:24.193
Hi, Doris.

44:24.195 --> 44:25.962
I wanted to talk to you
about the movie.

44:25.964 --> 44:29.165
I know it may all seem like
innocent fun,

44:29.167 --> 44:31.100
but the pastor of a
church has to

44:31.102 --> 44:34.537
maintain a higher
standard of decency.

44:34.539 --> 44:35.538
Right.

44:35.540 --> 44:37.106
You are so right.

44:37.108 --> 44:39.108
And, Doris, I just want you to
know you have my absolute

44:39.110 --> 44:43.112
word that we will only be
indecent when no one can see us.

44:45.149 --> 44:47.784
I was joking, I'm sorry.

44:47.786 --> 44:49.185
Amusing, I'm sure.

44:49.187 --> 44:51.387
Young lady, I have a
suggestion for you.

44:51.389 --> 44:54.524
Questions should be encouraged,
but in an environment that

44:54.526 --> 44:58.628
everyone can benefit from your
experience level.

44:58.630 --> 45:00.863
I think this church has the
perfect place

45:00.865 --> 45:04.634
for you and your questions.

45:04.636 --> 45:07.670
Right, okay, but I'm just
wondering how do they get two of

45:07.672 --> 45:10.339
every single animal on board
without any of them

45:10.341 --> 45:12.308
attacking and eating each other?

45:12.310 --> 45:13.810
And, really, more to the point,

45:13.812 --> 45:15.978
this is a story that is entirely
about genocide.

45:15.980 --> 45:19.982
Are we all okay with this being
about genocide?

45:20.651 --> 45:22.218
Good morning.

45:22.220 --> 45:26.089
Before we begin, I would just
like to say that I feel very

45:26.091 --> 45:30.126
confident that today's sermon
will be interruption-free.

45:31.195 --> 45:32.729
Let's turn to Matthew 7-7.

45:32.731 --> 45:36.232
Ben, excuse me, sorry.

45:36.234 --> 45:39.035
We just have a couple
of quick questions

45:39.037 --> 45:40.903
because our teacher didn't
answer them.

45:40.905 --> 45:44.941
[LAUGHTER]

45:45.609 --> 45:49.011
That is a really good one.

45:49.013 --> 45:50.346
Uh-huh.

45:50.348 --> 45:53.049
It's going to be a
list of questions.

45:53.051 --> 45:56.018
[MORE LAUGHTER]

45:56.020 --> 45:59.455
Bring it on.

45:59.457 --> 46:02.525
[MUSIC]

46:02.527 --> 46:04.861
Then there's all the family
stuff, there's...

46:04.863 --> 46:07.897
He's my ex-husband's
sister's husband,

46:07.899 --> 46:11.300
so that's like
we're in-laws, right?

46:11.302 --> 46:15.204
No, because we were once,
or twice, removed.

46:15.206 --> 46:16.072
It doesn't matter.

46:16.074 --> 46:19.575
My fear is that it's incest?

46:19.577 --> 46:20.977
It's not, though.

46:20.979 --> 46:24.614
Because we're not actually
related so I think

46:24.616 --> 46:27.383
if you really think it through,
it's probably,

46:27.385 --> 46:28.718
as I'm saying it out loud,

46:28.720 --> 46:30.153
I think it's probably
totally okay.

46:30.155 --> 46:31.587
This was really, helpful.

46:31.589 --> 46:35.625
Thank you for listening.

46:39.429 --> 46:43.466
I'll clear my,
I'll clear it here.

46:44.001 --> 46:44.901
Hey!

46:44.903 --> 46:46.068
Hey.

46:46.070 --> 46:47.770
Speak of the devil.

46:47.772 --> 46:49.472
Wait, no, can I say that?

46:49.474 --> 46:50.907
Yeah, I'll let it slide.

46:50.909 --> 46:53.109
Thank you.

46:53.111 --> 46:54.310
Am I too late for breakfast?

46:54.312 --> 46:55.411
I didn't know you were
going to join me.

46:55.413 --> 46:56.679
I would have waited.

46:56.681 --> 46:58.247
That's a lie, I wouldn't have.

46:58.249 --> 46:59.682
I was so hungry.

46:59.684 --> 47:01.317
Those kids, they really took it
out of me.

47:01.319 --> 47:02.852
You're really great with them,
you know?

47:02.854 --> 47:06.122
Well, I mean, I do have half of
an education degree.

47:06.124 --> 47:08.191
And you have
half a credit card.

47:08.193 --> 47:12.228
Your card was declined so I had
to cut it in half.

47:13.697 --> 47:15.498
I should have seen
this coming, right?

47:15.500 --> 47:17.166
Of course he's going to go
after the money.

47:17.168 --> 47:20.369
Yeah, Chaz has never been
really good at sharing.

47:20.371 --> 47:23.973
No, he has not.

47:23.975 --> 47:26.609
What, I'm supposed to give up
my coffee?

47:26.611 --> 47:29.478
My alone time with Daphne?

47:29.480 --> 47:33.349
No, the church could
use some help.

47:33.351 --> 47:37.220
A little bit in the office,
help out with the youth club?

47:37.222 --> 47:39.722
It would just be a few hours
here and there.

47:39.724 --> 47:40.790
Would you be my boss?

47:40.792 --> 47:41.991
Yes.

47:41.993 --> 47:43.392
Can I date my boss?

47:43.394 --> 47:44.560
Let me check.

47:44.562 --> 47:45.895
Yes.

47:45.897 --> 47:47.196
Yes, then I would
like this job.

47:47.198 --> 47:47.997
You would?

47:47.999 --> 47:49.065
Yes.

47:49.067 --> 47:49.799
Okay, what are
your qualifications.

47:49.801 --> 47:51.701
Oh, I'm adorable, and-

47:51.703 --> 47:53.569
Hired!

47:53.571 --> 47:55.204
[ALTOGETHER] Done.

47:55.206 --> 47:57.039
[LAUGHING]

47:57.041 --> 47:59.475
[JESSIE] No, I
completely understand.

47:59.477 --> 48:01.744
All guys are
like that, honestly.

48:01.746 --> 48:03.346
And I really hate to
break it to you,

48:03.348 --> 48:07.149
but they don't get any less
stupid as they age.

48:07.151 --> 48:10.386
Pretty much, it's a baseline,
it just keeps going.

48:10.388 --> 48:11.187
Jessie?

48:11.189 --> 48:12.054
Yeah?

48:12.056 --> 48:14.257
What if he doesn't like me?

48:14.259 --> 48:15.358
What?

48:15.360 --> 48:17.827
Alex, he's-

48:17.829 --> 48:19.161
You know what?

48:19.163 --> 48:21.497
I just read this story where
Jesus was talking

48:21.499 --> 48:23.499
about this pearl fisherman

48:23.501 --> 48:26.936
and he finds this beautiful,
amazing pearl.

48:26.938 --> 48:29.071
He sells everything that he has
so that he can

48:29.073 --> 48:31.040
buy this beauty, and he...

48:31.042 --> 48:34.944
Stay with me, what I'm saying
is, you're the pearl.

48:34.946 --> 48:37.847
So, if this boy is too stupid

48:37.849 --> 48:39.215
to see how beautiful you are,

48:39.217 --> 48:42.251
then, girl, that's his loss.

48:42.253 --> 48:44.020
Thanks.

48:44.022 --> 48:45.121
You're welcome.

48:45.123 --> 48:46.355
[CAR HORN HONKS OUTSIDE]

48:46.357 --> 48:47.924
That's your Dad.

48:47.926 --> 48:49.091
Bye guys.

48:49.093 --> 48:52.595
You're going to be here
next week, right?

48:52.597 --> 48:54.263
I hope so.

48:54.265 --> 48:55.064
Bye!

48:55.066 --> 48:58.901
Bye.

48:58.903 --> 49:00.603
Looks like you're having fun.

49:00.605 --> 49:02.805
I am, yes.

49:02.807 --> 49:04.073
Wait, though, if I'm having fun

49:04.075 --> 49:05.207
are you still going to pay me?

49:05.209 --> 49:06.542
No.

49:06.544 --> 49:10.546
Oh, then no, in that case
I am miserable.

49:10.881 --> 49:11.981
I can't believe
you're making me

49:11.983 --> 49:14.917
hang out with these
little monsters.

49:14.919 --> 49:18.988
So, is there any kind of reward
for a great first day?

49:23.260 --> 49:27.296
[MUSIC]

49:28.065 --> 49:30.766
What did you have in mind?

49:30.768 --> 49:34.804
Well, I was thinking...

49:48.819 --> 49:51.420
Let's get something to eat.

49:51.422 --> 49:55.424
[PIANO MUSIC]

49:59.096 --> 50:02.531
[JESSIE & BEN BANTER]

50:02.533 --> 50:03.699
[MOM] Jessie...

50:03.701 --> 50:07.737
[CHAZ] Hi honey, I'm home.

50:08.372 --> 50:09.638
What are you doing here?

50:09.640 --> 50:12.274
I was worried about my girl.

50:12.276 --> 50:13.609
Your girl?

50:13.611 --> 50:16.012
I'm not your girl.

50:16.014 --> 50:18.981
Why don't we all sit down and
talk this through.

50:18.983 --> 50:21.450
I'm sorry, Jess, maybe I made a
mistake by coming here.

50:21.452 --> 50:23.319
Right, well, we all know how
good you are

50:23.321 --> 50:25.187
at making mistakes.

50:25.189 --> 50:27.023
When you didn't sign the
divorce papers-

50:27.025 --> 50:29.125
Wait, wait.

50:29.127 --> 50:30.993
Of course, I signed them.

50:30.995 --> 50:32.161
I definitely signed them.

50:32.163 --> 50:33.829
I practically broke the
sound barrier by

50:33.831 --> 50:36.165
sprinting to the mailbox to get
them to you.

50:36.167 --> 50:37.633
Honey, I never got them.

50:37.635 --> 50:39.468
And when I didn't get them, I
thought that maybe

50:39.470 --> 50:40.870
you were having second thoughts.

50:40.872 --> 50:42.738
I was not having
second thoughts.

50:42.740 --> 50:44.306
I never even had
first thoughts.

50:44.308 --> 50:46.008
Any thoughts I might have had
about you,

50:46.010 --> 50:48.010
they were kind of centered
around dismemberment.

50:48.012 --> 50:48.878
Jessie-

50:48.880 --> 50:52.381
No, it's okay if she hates me.

50:52.383 --> 50:53.983
I hate me, too.

50:53.985 --> 50:55.084
But I'd hate myself more

50:55.086 --> 50:57.219
if I didn't try to
fix our marriage.

50:57.221 --> 50:59.188
We don't have a marriage.

50:59.190 --> 51:01.891
Legally, I'm still
your husband.

51:01.893 --> 51:03.826
No, that's what I'm trying to
say to you

51:03.828 --> 51:05.494
that you are not my husband.

51:05.496 --> 51:06.662
Jessie, will you just sit down

51:06.664 --> 51:08.998
and talk about this, please.

51:09.000 --> 51:11.367
No, I'm not going to sit down

51:11.369 --> 51:13.436
because there's nothing
to talk about.

51:13.438 --> 51:14.937
This is ridiculous.

51:14.939 --> 51:18.374
Maybe we should try to figure
this out.

51:18.376 --> 51:19.608
You want to figure this out?

51:19.610 --> 51:22.044
By all means, the three of you
can sit down

51:22.046 --> 51:23.279
and talk all night
if you want to.

51:23.281 --> 51:24.747
But I'm pretty clear on this.

51:24.749 --> 51:26.715
I'm beat, I'm going to bed.

51:26.717 --> 51:28.884
I had a great day today, in
case you're wondering,

51:28.886 --> 51:30.519
a great day.

51:30.521 --> 51:33.689
Thank you.

51:33.691 --> 51:37.026
Huh, okay.

51:37.028 --> 51:39.061
Well, you guys enjoy
your conversation.

51:39.063 --> 51:40.696
Thanks for coming by, Chaz.

51:40.698 --> 51:43.232
[BEN] Jessie, wait.

51:43.234 --> 51:47.303
[MOM] Let me go check on her.

51:49.072 --> 51:52.608
[SIGH] Wow, Ben, I've got to
say I'm pretty surprised.

51:52.610 --> 51:56.645
Yeah, I'm surprised, too, Chaz.

51:57.714 --> 52:01.283
You really trying to
fix your marriage?

52:01.285 --> 52:05.387
I mean, first you had my
sister, and now my wife?

52:05.389 --> 52:06.755
What's next?

52:06.757 --> 52:10.292
I don't have any pets.

52:10.294 --> 52:12.094
Careful, Charlie.

52:12.096 --> 52:13.929
I just hope that the church
doesn't find out that their

52:13.931 --> 52:17.967
pastor is running around with a
married woman.

52:30.413 --> 52:31.647
So what did she say?

52:31.649 --> 52:33.582
Oh, she is not talking to
anybody tonight.

52:33.584 --> 52:37.586
She is locked in her room.

52:37.588 --> 52:40.089
I don't think you're going to
get her back, babe.

52:40.091 --> 52:41.490
She's been really hurt.

52:41.492 --> 52:42.992
I know, Mom.

52:42.994 --> 52:44.793
Will you please just
talk to her?

52:44.795 --> 52:47.363
Please.

52:47.365 --> 52:49.498
Just give it a
little time, okay?

52:49.500 --> 52:52.268
Let her cool down and I'll talk
to her in the morning,

52:52.270 --> 52:53.269
all right?

52:53.271 --> 52:54.436
Thank you.

52:54.438 --> 52:55.337
Thank you so much.

52:55.339 --> 52:57.139
Okay.

52:57.141 --> 53:01.177
[MUSIC]

53:01.878 --> 53:05.881
[BUBBLEWRAP POPPING]

53:10.887 --> 53:13.455
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

53:13.457 --> 53:17.459
Woah, save some for the china.

53:18.461 --> 53:20.729
Honey, he's really
hurting, too.

53:20.731 --> 53:23.632
Couldn't you just
go talk to him?

53:23.634 --> 53:26.068
What did he say to you?

53:26.070 --> 53:30.139
He really wants to make amends
and maybe...

53:30.141 --> 53:31.974
I'm not saying,
"Get back together".

53:31.976 --> 53:35.978
I'm just saying, that maybe you
can forgive him?

53:41.585 --> 53:42.918
Where is he?

53:42.920 --> 53:46.956
He's in his old bedroom up in
the attic.

53:53.763 --> 53:57.800
What are you up to?

54:00.737 --> 54:03.239
I can't get over you.

54:03.241 --> 54:05.040
You look amazing.

54:05.042 --> 54:07.009
There's something different
about you.

54:07.011 --> 54:08.577
Well, I am trying
a new moisturizer.

54:08.579 --> 54:10.212
It's balancing out my T zone.

54:10.214 --> 54:11.780
Okay, there you are.

54:11.782 --> 54:13.415
Joke about everything.

54:13.417 --> 54:15.517
Well, you, my dear,
haven't changed.

54:15.519 --> 54:18.587
Actually, I have.

54:18.589 --> 54:20.556
I've been seeing someone.

54:20.558 --> 54:21.957
Just one?

54:21.959 --> 54:23.092
That is different.

54:23.094 --> 54:25.127
No, it's not like that, it's...

54:25.129 --> 54:27.263
I've been seeing a counselor.

54:27.265 --> 54:31.267
And he says that, in order to
fix my soul,

54:31.269 --> 54:33.569
I need to mend the things that
I've broken.

54:33.571 --> 54:36.305
Starting with our marriage.

54:36.307 --> 54:37.806
We are not married, Chaz.

54:37.808 --> 54:39.608
Legally, we are.

54:39.610 --> 54:42.378
And people in this town might
say that,

54:42.380 --> 54:44.113
in the eyes of God,
we still are.

54:44.115 --> 54:46.415
Right, but those same
people would say

54:46.417 --> 54:47.616
that you have three wives.

54:47.618 --> 54:49.551
Had.

54:49.553 --> 54:52.421
But really only one that I
still love.

54:52.423 --> 54:54.623
Jessie, we were
really good once.

54:54.625 --> 54:57.726
And I want to get that back.

54:57.728 --> 54:59.928
And I'm willing to do anything.

54:59.930 --> 55:03.966
Anything to fix us.

55:04.734 --> 55:08.704
That is, literally all that I
ever wanted you to say Chaz...

55:10.440 --> 55:13.075
before you cheated.

55:13.077 --> 55:16.145
Now it's just irritating.

55:16.147 --> 55:18.013
You're not Sarah, you know
that, right?

55:18.015 --> 55:19.148
What?

55:19.150 --> 55:20.649
People like Ben,
they go for Sarahs.

55:20.651 --> 55:24.787
Not for girls like you.

55:24.789 --> 55:28.824
And there you are.

55:39.936 --> 55:43.939
[SIGH]

55:49.512 --> 55:53.549
Hey.

55:59.289 --> 56:01.023
So...

56:01.025 --> 56:03.559
So.

56:03.561 --> 56:07.596
Yeah.

56:09.999 --> 56:13.402
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

56:13.404 --> 56:14.803
Sorry.

56:14.805 --> 56:17.139
We didn't realize you
were in conference,

56:17.141 --> 56:19.241
with a woman,
with the door closed.

56:19.243 --> 56:21.243
There's nothing going on in
here, Doris.

56:21.245 --> 56:22.378
That's a shame.

56:22.380 --> 56:24.980
I should go.

56:24.982 --> 56:27.216
Since I'm sure you want
to talk about me.

56:27.218 --> 56:31.253
No, it's not about you.

56:32.922 --> 56:34.256
It's about her.

56:34.258 --> 56:35.991
I know, she interrupts church.

56:35.993 --> 56:37.393
It's an embarrassment.

56:37.395 --> 56:39.228
Attendance has been way up.

56:39.230 --> 56:41.597
We've been hearing some very
upsetting things-

56:41.599 --> 56:44.333
We're concerned about
your intentions.

56:44.335 --> 56:48.337
And how those intentions
reflect on the church.

56:52.709 --> 56:54.209
I mean, if I would have known
she would come to this town

56:54.211 --> 56:55.244
and cause this much trouble,

56:55.246 --> 56:56.545
I never would have
had her come.

56:56.547 --> 56:58.013
You couldn't have known, honey.

56:58.015 --> 56:59.882
I just want to
make things right.

56:59.884 --> 57:01.683
I feel like she's making me to
be the bad guy

57:01.685 --> 57:04.353
and this is my town, this is
where I grew up.

57:04.355 --> 57:05.888
We're here for you.

57:05.890 --> 57:08.023
All of us.

57:08.025 --> 57:09.725
I'm going to do
the right thing.

57:09.727 --> 57:12.194
You're going to be at church on
Sunday, yeah?

57:12.196 --> 57:14.930
I'm wherever you are, honey.

57:14.932 --> 57:18.967
Thank you, Daphne.

57:20.770 --> 57:22.237
[PASTOR] Good
morning, everyone.

57:22.239 --> 57:23.238
[AUDIENCE] Good morning.

57:23.240 --> 57:25.974
Now, I know that many of you

57:25.976 --> 57:28.644
may have some questions today.

57:28.646 --> 57:31.447
That's great, but with so many
people here,

57:31.449 --> 57:35.484
we ask that you use the cards

57:37.153 --> 57:39.054
provided in the pews to-

57:39.056 --> 57:41.457
Actually, do you mind if I
share what I wrote?

57:41.459 --> 57:43.158
I do, Chaz, the point
was to wait.

57:43.160 --> 57:47.196
I truly am grateful to
be here today.

57:47.630 --> 57:50.732
Many of you knew me as a kid

57:50.734 --> 57:54.636
and all the mistakes
that I made.

57:54.638 --> 57:56.104
Well, I'm here today because
I'm trying to get my life

57:56.106 --> 57:57.973
back on the right path.

57:57.975 --> 58:00.509
You got all that to fit
on your card?

58:00.511 --> 58:04.246
Obviously I need
everyone's prayers.

58:04.248 --> 58:07.449
Especially for my wife and me.

58:07.451 --> 58:09.651
Ex-wife.

58:09.653 --> 58:11.487
One of several, actually.

58:11.489 --> 58:12.621
Charlie, why don't
you sit down-

58:12.623 --> 58:15.357
No, Mom, I just need to know,

58:15.359 --> 58:18.193
how am I supposed to
fix my marriage

58:18.195 --> 58:22.231
when my wife is being lusted
after by your pastor?

58:23.766 --> 58:26.368
Again, ex-wife.

58:26.370 --> 58:27.669
Which is because of you.

58:27.671 --> 58:29.471
We can fix it, Jess.

58:29.473 --> 58:31.640
Malachi 2-16.

58:31.642 --> 58:34.142
God says he hates divorce.

58:34.144 --> 58:37.446
And Matthew 5 allows it if
someone is unfaithful.

58:37.448 --> 58:40.716
That's if he cheats
on you, Jezebel.

58:40.718 --> 58:44.753
He did cheat on me.

58:45.655 --> 58:47.723
And don't call me Jezebel.

58:47.725 --> 58:48.857
That's a bad thing, right?

58:48.859 --> 58:50.459
Jezebel?

58:50.461 --> 58:52.661
Alright, I'm glad everyone's
learning their Bible, but Chaz

58:52.663 --> 58:55.864
I think this is a conversation
to be had in private.

58:55.866 --> 58:59.535
Actually it effects all of us
if you use church funds to

58:59.537 --> 59:03.338
fool around with a married woman
in your office.

59:03.340 --> 59:04.806
That has never happened.

59:04.808 --> 59:07.743
[AUDIENCE ARGUES]

59:07.745 --> 59:11.780
[LOUD WHISTLE]

59:12.415 --> 59:14.983
To all of our guests,
we apologize.

59:14.985 --> 59:18.487
This embarrassment was to be
addressed after the service,

59:18.489 --> 59:22.457
but I can see something has to
be done right away.

59:23.393 --> 59:25.694
Pastor Kingston,
please step down.

59:25.696 --> 59:28.564
[MOM] Doris, Ben has done
absolutely nothing wrong-

59:28.566 --> 59:31.033
The committee has
already decided.

59:31.035 --> 59:32.668
He cannot be the pastor

59:32.670 --> 59:34.603
as long as he's under this
woman's spell.

59:34.605 --> 59:36.204
Doris, I am so sick of you
talking to Jessie like-

59:36.206 --> 59:37.940
No, no, no.

59:37.942 --> 59:39.274
You see what you're
doing, right?

59:39.276 --> 59:40.909
This is exactly what he wanted.

59:40.911 --> 59:42.244
Are you just here to hurt us?

59:42.246 --> 59:43.579
Jess...

59:43.581 --> 59:46.415
Jessie, Charlie's heart is in
the right place.

59:46.417 --> 59:48.917
Can't you tell he's
suffering, too?

59:48.919 --> 59:50.118
This guy is suffering?

59:50.120 --> 59:51.186
I don't think so.

59:51.188 --> 59:52.688
That is the face of pure evil.

59:52.690 --> 59:54.222
Jessie,

59:54.224 --> 59:58.260
I love you but he's my son.

59:58.528 --> 01:00:02.531
Okay, you're right.

01:00:03.299 --> 01:00:05.400
He is your son.

01:00:05.402 --> 01:00:07.736
I'm sorry, everyone.

01:00:07.738 --> 01:00:11.807
I just realized that I don't
have a place here.

01:00:16.713 --> 01:00:20.282
I release your pastor
from my spell.

01:00:20.284 --> 01:00:24.319
[PASTOR] Jessie!

01:00:26.222 --> 01:00:30.192
[MUSIC]

01:00:33.896 --> 01:00:36.798
Jessie, stop!

01:00:36.800 --> 01:00:38.433
You should go back inside, Ben.

01:00:38.435 --> 01:00:39.901
I didn't even realize
this before,

01:00:39.903 --> 01:00:41.670
but you are really
needed in there.

01:00:41.672 --> 01:00:42.838
They are pretty messed up.

01:00:42.840 --> 01:00:45.073
I'm not worried about them
right now.

01:00:45.075 --> 01:00:48.110
Do you even realize what just
happened in there?

01:00:48.112 --> 01:00:50.112
I just got you fired
from a church.

01:00:50.114 --> 01:00:51.680
Chaz did that, okay?

01:00:51.682 --> 01:00:52.748
And that will blow over.

01:00:52.750 --> 01:00:55.584
No one listens to Chaz.

01:00:55.586 --> 01:00:57.085
You'll get your divorce.

01:00:57.087 --> 01:01:00.122
And you and I, we can pick up
right where we left off.

01:01:00.124 --> 01:01:03.125
Let's talk about where we left
off, actually, Ben.

01:01:03.127 --> 01:01:04.459
Because you are totally right.

01:01:04.461 --> 01:01:05.861
My divorce is going to go away.

01:01:05.863 --> 01:01:07.529
It's going to be finalized and
it's going to be done.

01:01:07.531 --> 01:01:10.365
But you...

01:01:10.367 --> 01:01:12.768
Do you even realize that you're
wearing your wedding ring?

01:01:12.770 --> 01:01:16.004
That every single day you have
worn your wedding ring?

01:01:16.006 --> 01:01:19.041
When you kiss me, it's on.

01:01:19.043 --> 01:01:21.176
My marriage is done,
Ben, it's over.

01:01:21.178 --> 01:01:24.646
But you have been wearing that
ring ever since I got here.

01:01:24.648 --> 01:01:28.617
Every time you've kissed me,
that has been on your finger.

01:01:29.352 --> 01:01:30.852
It's not about Chaz.

01:01:30.854 --> 01:01:33.789
Ben, you're not the other man.

01:01:33.791 --> 01:01:37.159
I'm the other woman.

01:01:37.161 --> 01:01:41.129
And I'm not going
to do it anymore.

01:01:44.734 --> 01:01:48.770
[MUSIC SWELLS]

01:01:57.413 --> 01:02:01.450
[MUSIC]

01:02:34.350 --> 01:02:38.320
[PIANO MUSIC]

01:03:20.263 --> 01:03:24.299
[PIANO MUSIC]

01:04:06.676 --> 01:04:10.712
[DOOR BELL]

01:04:12.782 --> 01:04:14.149
Excuse me.

01:04:14.151 --> 01:04:16.718
I'm sorry, I'm looking
for Chaz Ellis.

01:04:16.720 --> 01:04:18.220
He isn't here right now.

01:04:18.222 --> 01:04:19.387
Can I help you?

01:04:19.389 --> 01:04:21.723
I'm his mother.

01:04:21.725 --> 01:04:23.658
Oh, thank goodness you're not
the squatter.

01:04:23.660 --> 01:04:25.227
The squatter?

01:04:25.229 --> 01:04:27.362
He really did get the old bag
to pack up.

01:04:27.364 --> 01:04:29.631
He said he would but I half
didn't believe him.

01:04:29.633 --> 01:04:31.533
Is he here because we were
supposed to meet at the diner

01:04:31.535 --> 01:04:32.634
and he didn't show-

01:04:32.636 --> 01:04:34.302
I'm sorry, you are?

01:04:34.304 --> 01:04:37.205
Jim Nueford, I'm sure Chaz has
mentioned me.

01:04:37.207 --> 01:04:38.340
Of course.

01:04:38.342 --> 01:04:39.741
You aught to be proud
of that boy.

01:04:39.743 --> 01:04:40.976
The amount he negotiated

01:04:40.978 --> 01:04:43.979
to broker the close
of this last holdout,

01:04:43.981 --> 01:04:45.680
just between you and me,

01:04:45.682 --> 01:04:49.351
we're paying more to him than
we are for the house.

01:04:49.353 --> 01:04:51.486
I'm sorry, did I just say
something wrong?

01:04:51.488 --> 01:04:55.490
Would you come
in a minute, please?

01:04:56.192 --> 01:05:00.161
[MUSIC]

01:05:20.583 --> 01:05:22.017
Hey Daphne.

01:05:22.019 --> 01:05:23.551
What are you doing?

01:05:23.553 --> 01:05:26.288
Practicing my talent for the Ms.
Virginia pageant.

01:05:26.290 --> 01:05:27.422
Isn't it obvious?

01:05:27.424 --> 01:05:29.691
Whoa, Daphne, what's wrong?

01:05:29.693 --> 01:05:32.193
You tricked me into spreading
rumors about her.

01:05:32.195 --> 01:05:34.095
Whoa, I didn't ask you
to do anything.

01:05:34.097 --> 01:05:36.431
The only thing that Jessie
ever did wrong

01:05:36.433 --> 01:05:38.967
was fall for you.

01:05:38.969 --> 01:05:42.237
But I guess we
all make mistakes.

01:05:42.239 --> 01:05:43.138
You know I was going to ask you

01:05:43.140 --> 01:05:44.739
to come to New York with me,

01:05:44.741 --> 01:05:46.641
but I guess you want to be a
waitress in a dead end diner.

01:05:46.643 --> 01:05:50.679
[DINER CROWD HUSHES]

01:05:50.980 --> 01:05:53.415
I own this dead
end diner, Chaz.

01:05:53.417 --> 01:05:54.316
I bought it three years ago

01:05:54.318 --> 01:05:56.918
and it makes me a lot of money.

01:05:56.920 --> 01:05:59.754
But even if I were,
"just a waitress",

01:05:59.756 --> 01:06:03.792
I wouldn't waste one more
minute on you.

01:06:04.060 --> 01:06:06.728
So I guess the special's
out of the question?

01:06:06.730 --> 01:06:10.298
Oh no, let me get that
for you, sweetie.

01:06:10.300 --> 01:06:14.336
One special - to go!

01:06:23.179 --> 01:06:24.813
What are you still
doing here, Chaz?

01:06:24.815 --> 01:06:27.782
Shouldn't you be winning
back your wife?

01:06:27.784 --> 01:06:29.951
Oh, don't worry, Benny, I've
still got plenty of leftovers

01:06:29.953 --> 01:06:33.355
you can pick through.

01:06:33.357 --> 01:06:35.323
[MUSIC]

01:06:35.325 --> 01:06:41.396
[DISHES CRASHING]

01:06:42.498 --> 01:06:46.534
[DAPHNE] What are you doing?!

01:06:50.873 --> 01:06:52.607
[DORIS] Pastor Kingston!

01:06:52.609 --> 01:06:54.542
[ALTOGETHER] He started it!

01:06:54.544 --> 01:06:55.810
Even with the young woman gone,

01:06:55.812 --> 01:06:59.547
I can see her influence is still
corrupting you.

01:06:59.549 --> 01:07:03.051
Perhaps a vote for revocation
is still in order.

01:07:03.053 --> 01:07:04.786
I recommend you
prepare a sermon-

01:07:04.788 --> 01:07:07.555
No, you know what?

01:07:07.557 --> 01:07:11.593
I'll prepare my own sermon.

01:07:17.833 --> 01:07:21.903
[PIANO MUSIC / TRAFFIC SOUNDS]

01:07:32.915 --> 01:07:36.951
[CHURCH BELLS]

01:07:55.204 --> 01:07:57.005
Hey Mom.

01:07:57.007 --> 01:07:58.840
Sorry I'm late.

01:07:58.842 --> 01:08:01.409
Now what happened?

01:08:01.411 --> 01:08:05.447
The moving truck will be here
any second.

01:08:06.048 --> 01:08:10.085
I met your friend Mr. Nueford.

01:08:18.761 --> 01:08:22.796
This was the last lot they
needed in order to build.

01:08:23.933 --> 01:08:28.002
I saw an opportunity
and I took it.

01:08:31.240 --> 01:08:34.075
How bad is it,
your money problems?

01:08:34.077 --> 01:08:36.877
Look, I had an investment.

01:08:36.880 --> 01:08:39.481
It was a sure-fire thing, and
then the economy-

01:08:39.483 --> 01:08:43.518
You don't love her, do you?

01:08:45.787 --> 01:08:49.858
You just needed me
to leave here.

01:08:54.729 --> 01:08:56.898
Well, I am sorry.

01:08:56.899 --> 01:09:00.001
For what?

01:09:00.002 --> 01:09:02.337
I'm not leaving, Charlie.

01:09:02.339 --> 01:09:06.374
Bethel Cove is my home.

01:09:06.774 --> 01:09:08.609
Mom, please don't
start this again.

01:09:08.612 --> 01:09:10.278
My community is here.

01:09:10.279 --> 01:09:12.147
My church is here, Dad and
Sarah are here-

01:09:12.149 --> 01:09:15.483
No, they're not, Mom,
they're dead!

01:09:15.484 --> 01:09:19.520
I'm all you've got left, and
I'm not here.

01:09:20.990 --> 01:09:24.692
Mom, if the house
isn't empty tonight-

01:09:24.694 --> 01:09:28.729
I'm not leaving.

01:09:30.332 --> 01:09:34.368
You can have the house,

01:09:34.937 --> 01:09:38.907
but you have to let Jessie go.

01:09:39.375 --> 01:09:43.411
You're going to choose
Jessie over me?

01:09:43.679 --> 01:09:45.712
Family's not about
choosing sides.

01:09:45.715 --> 01:09:49.283
That's all this has been about!

01:09:49.286 --> 01:09:52.953
Let her be.

01:09:52.956 --> 01:09:53.854
You know what?

01:09:53.857 --> 01:09:55.223
Doesn't matter.

01:09:55.225 --> 01:09:59.260
It's fine.

01:10:00.863 --> 01:10:04.899
So, I guess we have a deal.

01:10:05.668 --> 01:10:08.169
Someday you're going to
want to come home.

01:10:08.171 --> 01:10:11.339
And your pride's going to get
in your way.

01:10:11.341 --> 01:10:13.575
And you're going to feel

01:10:13.577 --> 01:10:16.811
that it's too late.

01:10:16.813 --> 01:10:20.815
It's never too late.

01:10:31.427 --> 01:10:35.430
[CHURCH BELLS]

01:10:39.768 --> 01:10:43.805
[PIANO MUSIC]

01:11:25.481 --> 01:11:29.517
What have you got against me?

01:11:35.257 --> 01:11:36.891
I'm sorry, I didn't-

01:11:36.893 --> 01:11:38.159
I know the tone.

01:11:38.161 --> 01:11:40.395
I've had conversations like
that myself.

01:11:40.397 --> 01:11:41.996
Please, go ahead.

01:11:41.998 --> 01:11:43.498
No, I don't need to.

01:11:43.500 --> 01:11:45.600
I haven't eaten chocolate
for a year.

01:11:45.602 --> 01:11:48.269
And I'm still gaining weight!

01:11:48.271 --> 01:11:51.773
The acoustics in here are great
for shouting.

01:11:51.775 --> 01:11:55.076
They're even better
for listening.

01:11:55.078 --> 01:11:59.080
Stay as long as you need.

01:12:11.026 --> 01:12:15.063
[MUSIC]

01:12:30.379 --> 01:12:34.415
I'm lost.

01:12:38.821 --> 01:12:41.322
I don't know if you're there,

01:12:41.324 --> 01:12:45.360
but if you are,

01:12:45.661 --> 01:12:49.364
could you just tell me
where to go?

01:12:52.701 --> 01:12:56.738
I'm listening.

01:13:01.810 --> 01:13:05.813
[SONG]

01:13:32.374 --> 01:13:36.411
Okay, let's talk.

01:14:24.259 --> 01:14:26.227
Good morning.

01:14:26.229 --> 01:14:28.429
Good morning.

01:14:28.431 --> 01:14:30.264
It looks like you had
quite a night.

01:14:30.266 --> 01:14:31.899
I did.

01:14:31.901 --> 01:14:33.801
Coffee, thank God.

01:14:33.803 --> 01:14:37.839
And the man who works for Him.

01:14:40.642 --> 01:14:43.511
You don't have any Tobasco
sauce, do you?

01:14:43.513 --> 01:14:47.548
No, I'm sorry.

01:14:47.850 --> 01:14:52.019
So, are you still angry?

01:14:52.021 --> 01:14:55.690
Yes, I'm still very angry.

01:14:55.692 --> 01:14:58.025
But I realized something
last night.

01:14:58.027 --> 01:15:01.329
You can't be mad at someone you
don't believe in.

01:15:01.331 --> 01:15:04.098
Yeah, very cool.

01:15:04.100 --> 01:15:05.533
[PHONE BUZZING]

01:15:05.535 --> 01:15:09.604
You should probably get that.

01:15:09.606 --> 01:15:12.940
Somebody's very popular.

01:15:12.942 --> 01:15:15.009
I guess so.

01:15:21.049 --> 01:15:23.184
[PASTOR] The good shepherd,

01:15:23.186 --> 01:15:26.821
that's what Jesus
called himself.

01:15:26.823 --> 01:15:30.858
And he shared with us a parable
about a good shepherd.

01:15:31.960 --> 01:15:35.930
Who left his entire flock to
seek out one single lost sheep.

01:15:36.965 --> 01:15:39.233
Why?

01:15:39.235 --> 01:15:42.069
Was he just really bad at math?

01:15:42.071 --> 01:15:44.005
[AUDIENCE CHUCKLES]

01:15:44.007 --> 01:15:48.042
Or maybe, he knew that
everyone matters.

01:15:49.011 --> 01:15:53.047
Somehow, especially,
the lost ones.

01:15:56.318 --> 01:16:00.321
We recently had a lost sheep.

01:16:00.822 --> 01:16:04.225
Only she didn't wander off.

01:16:04.227 --> 01:16:05.927
We pushed her away.

01:16:05.929 --> 01:16:09.730
Claiming she was
a bad influence.

01:16:09.732 --> 01:16:13.768
How could she be
a bad influence?

01:16:14.369 --> 01:16:17.271
She inspired me.

01:16:17.273 --> 01:16:20.007
How could she be
a bad influence?

01:16:20.009 --> 01:16:24.011
She filled these pews.

01:16:24.446 --> 01:16:26.881
I'm going to find Jessie.

01:16:26.883 --> 01:16:30.918
And if that is me giving in to
a bad influence,

01:16:31.453 --> 01:16:35.122
well then,

01:16:35.124 --> 01:16:39.126
I quit.

01:16:41.396 --> 01:16:45.433
[JESSIE CLEARS HER THROAT]

01:16:45.968 --> 01:16:48.569
I'm sorry to interrupt.

01:16:48.571 --> 01:16:50.871
Hi.

01:16:50.873 --> 01:16:54.875
Hi.

01:16:55.277 --> 01:16:57.945
I got your messages.

01:16:57.947 --> 01:17:00.114
And I got your messages.

01:17:00.116 --> 01:17:02.316
And your messages.

01:17:02.318 --> 01:17:04.752
And I called my Mom.

01:17:04.754 --> 01:17:08.823
And she told me that you
trashed the diner?

01:17:09.224 --> 01:17:12.927
And that you had this whole
plan to quit your job,

01:17:12.929 --> 01:17:16.397
so I thought that I should come
here in person,

01:17:16.399 --> 01:17:17.665
and tell you that I-

01:17:17.667 --> 01:17:19.967
[MOM] Come on.

01:17:19.969 --> 01:17:23.471
Right, okay.

01:17:23.473 --> 01:17:26.507
Hello, everyone.

01:17:26.509 --> 01:17:29.176
I wanted to say, in person,
that I think

01:17:29.178 --> 01:17:32.246
that a food fighting preacher
is awesome.

01:17:32.248 --> 01:17:34.682
[LAUGHTER]

01:17:34.684 --> 01:17:38.719
And I think it's probably
something that this town needs.

01:17:39.421 --> 01:17:40.321
Yeah?

01:17:40.323 --> 01:17:42.790
[AUDIENCE] Yeah.

01:17:42.792 --> 01:17:45.292
Because we all learn from you.

01:17:45.294 --> 01:17:49.096
Like how you taught me with
God, I'm never alone.

01:17:49.098 --> 01:17:52.433
I know that now.

01:17:52.435 --> 01:17:54.769
So I think you should stay.

01:17:54.771 --> 01:17:57.271
And I think I should stay.

01:17:57.273 --> 01:17:59.640
And I promise I will take as
much or as little of you

01:17:59.642 --> 01:18:00.608
as you give to me.

01:18:00.610 --> 01:18:03.310
I'm sorry that I pushed you.

01:18:03.312 --> 01:18:07.348
I needed you to push me.

01:18:07.816 --> 01:18:11.852
I needed you.

01:18:15.624 --> 01:18:18.125
Oh, no ring.

01:18:18.127 --> 01:18:20.061
You really were
coming after me.

01:18:20.063 --> 01:18:22.897
Oh yeah, truck's all packed up.

01:18:22.899 --> 01:18:26.167
[DORIS] Pastor, we
have a question.

01:18:26.169 --> 01:18:29.970
Yeah, you guys going to ever
kiss, or what?

01:18:29.972 --> 01:18:33.974
[LAUGHTER]

01:18:34.710 --> 01:18:38.746
[MUSIC / APPLAUSE]

01:18:47.089 --> 01:18:48.723
Doris, that was my
kind of question.

01:18:48.725 --> 01:18:50.091
Yes, more questions, please.

01:18:50.093 --> 01:18:54.128
[LAUGHTER]

01:18:55.597 --> 01:18:59.033
[PIANO MUSIC]

01:18:59.035 --> 01:19:02.103
We are going to be late, again.

01:19:02.105 --> 01:19:03.237
We are not going to be late.

01:19:03.239 --> 01:19:05.106
You know I like to
make an entrance.

01:19:05.108 --> 01:19:06.607
Anyway, it's not my fault.

01:19:06.609 --> 01:19:10.644
M was up crying half the night.

01:19:10.846 --> 01:19:14.815
[MOM TO BABY] Okay, Mr.,
let's go.

01:19:16.184 --> 01:19:19.086
Are you ready to
interrupt your Daddy?

01:19:19.088 --> 01:19:20.421
Just like your Mommy.

01:19:20.423 --> 01:19:22.790
Ha.

01:19:22.792 --> 01:19:24.258
Hi.

01:19:24.260 --> 01:19:26.427
Oh, I wrote some jokes for you.

01:19:26.429 --> 01:19:28.929
No, I have my own.

01:19:28.931 --> 01:19:30.397
Those are funny jokes.

01:19:30.399 --> 01:19:33.200
So maybe do those instead?

01:19:33.202 --> 01:19:35.069
Okay, yeah, I'll try.

01:19:35.071 --> 01:19:37.138
Hello!

01:19:37.140 --> 01:19:41.175
Come on, come on,
the service is starting.

01:19:41.376 --> 01:19:43.410
[CHOIR SINGING]
 This is the day,

01:19:43.412 --> 01:19:45.312
 this is the day,

01:19:45.314 --> 01:19:47.982
 that the Lord has made,

01:19:47.984 --> 01:19:51.085
 that the Lord has made,

01:19:51.087 --> 01:19:53.621
 I will rejoice,

01:19:53.623 --> 01:19:55.589
 I will rejoice,

01:19:55.591 --> 01:19:58.259
 and be glad in it,

01:19:58.261 --> 01:20:01.495
 and be glad in it.

01:20:01.497 --> 01:20:05.533
 This is the day that the
Lord has made,

01:20:06.668 --> 01:20:10.704
 I will rejoice
and be glad in it,

01:20:11.907 --> 01:20:14.441
 This is the day,

01:20:14.443 --> 01:20:16.343
 this is the day,

01:20:16.345 --> 01:20:20.381
 that the Lord has made!

01:20:23.318 --> 01:20:27.354
[APPLAUSE]

01:20:30.158 --> 01:20:31.158
Good morning.

01:20:31.160 --> 01:20:32.426
[AUDIENCE] Good morning.

01:20:32.428 --> 01:20:33.961
Welcome.

01:20:33.963 --> 01:20:36.430
Just like always, we will be
starting with the town hall

01:20:36.432 --> 01:20:38.499
portion of the service.

01:20:38.501 --> 01:20:40.601
And since we owe it all to her,

01:20:40.603 --> 01:20:43.971
I'm going to ask my beautiful
wife, Jessie, to host.

01:20:43.973 --> 01:20:45.139
Thank you, sweetie.

01:20:45.141 --> 01:20:46.874
You're welcome.

01:20:46.876 --> 01:20:48.475
Okay, so let's start with a

01:20:48.477 --> 01:20:52.513
non-crossword related inquiry,
okay Eddie?

01:20:52.714 --> 01:20:56.750
Any other questions, guys?

01:20:57.853 --> 01:20:59.019
Okay.

01:20:59.021 --> 01:21:01.155
Alright, let's get started.

01:21:01.157 --> 01:21:04.225
Coming right over here...

